"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Hands down best place for oysters and lobster roll on the east coast!  My husband and I took a trip to the New England states for one week.  We traveled from Boston to Maine by car.  We tried oysters and lobster roll in every state, at famous eateries showcased on TV.  However, our favorite place was a recommendation by my husband&#39;s coworkers, Neptune Oyster.  Not only do they have an impressive selection of delicious oysters from both coasts, the lobster roll beat out everything we tried in Maine.  What made this place better than the rest was temperature.  The lobster roll was actually warm - both the buttered lobster meat and the bun!  I like raw seafood cold but I HATE cooked seafood served tepid or worse, cold (e.g. shrimp cocktail).  So if you&#39;re in the mood for great seafood, skip Maine and go straight to Boston!  <br><br>Warning: there will be a long wait (like 1.5 to 2 hours) but they give you a pager so you can leave and go do other things (like nap, grab drinks elsewhere or take a pre-dinner stroll).",
