"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This place always seems to be a great place for friends to get together after work, bring visitors from near and far; and for a special place for a date. <br><br>Today was my umpteenth time going and was still the friendly and satisfying visit I&#39;ve come to expect. <br><br>We were greeted promptly and the interior warms you up and makes you feel cozy. <br><br>There&#39;s inside and enclosed outside seating. My friend and I opted for the outside since it was a warm early-afternoon Monday. <br><br>Our rather attractive waitress was quick and sincere upon the greet. She filled our water glasses and offered bread. We placed &#34;Blueberry Thrill&#34; martini orders and checked out the familiar and diverse menu. <br>(The drinks have been off the menu a few months, but they still made them for us anyway - really nice)<br><br>I ordered the Standard burger and my friend ordered the grilled cheese. We sipped our tasty drinks and talked and watched the people walk by. <br><br>For our next drink, we both get cosmos and they were nothing short of delicious. Our food arrived promptly and the plates looked great. My burger was prepared correctly and was juicy and flavorful. The string fries accompaniment looked appetizing, but could&#39;ve used a tad less salt, but otherwise good. <br><br>As our waitress cleared the plates, she asked about dessert. We split the Butterscotch Bread Pudding. OMG. This is so good! I couldn&#39;t stop eating it!<br><br>The summary - great location, great service, great drinks, great food and AWESOME desserts. This place is a must.",
