"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Gawwd, that was good!  You&#39;d think waiting for 1.5hrs for a table would build expectations to some kind of holy grail of yelp unattainable level. But what greeted me after the wait was probably the best brunch I&#39;ve  had in the city. Why?  The food is unique. The flavors are packed. The bread is so delicious and the portions are huge. I ordered the Ole Miss and the bread was this cayenne pepper spiced loaf. Big, thick pieces, with a very creative, extremely tasty and complimentary mango sour cream. The hash browns were the right amount of browned crisp and soft. And the eggs that topped the bread were just right -- soft scrambled, not runny, moist. The decor in the place is fun to look at while you eat, and the service was awesome despite how packed they were. My coffee mug was constantly filled and the servers were friendly, patient, attentive ... Despite huge lines. <br><br>A brunch experience not to be missed. Delicious, delicious food that&#39;s creative, really well priced, and way more flavorful than any other restaurant in the city. Loved it.",
