"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"It&#39;s almost semi-iconic to dine al fresco style at Stephanie&#39;s. I mean you can&#39;t walk down Newbury street and not notice that this place is always crawling with good looking people eating with their sunglasses on!! <br><br>We made the last minute decision to eat here and made reservations without any issues for 5pm for a group of 4 on a Saturday. <br><br>TIP: Reservations are mainly for indoor dining, if you&#39;re looking to sit outside that&#39;s with the outdoor hostess (which I might add was not pleasant at all) but luckily someone switched with her when we had to go back outside to get a seat. We were seated within a minute of asking. We probably made it before the rush. <br><br>My group was highly satisfied with their meals and left us so full!! (we were at a brewery tour earlier that afternoon too :]) We had:<br><br>-- Stephanie&#39;s Lobster salad Roll<br>-- Oversized Stephi burger<br>-- Pulled Chicken Pasta <br>-- Cuban sandwich<br><br>I have to say that my craving for the lobster roll has been SATISFIED and for $27 it was well worth the price. It was overloaded with lobster cuts and there was justtttt enough mayo that I forgot it was there. You get a huge side of fries plus cole slaw and it was the best combo. I really enjoyed it and had no regrets. <br><br>We had the pitcher of white sangria and ehhh maybe we should have gone with the red sangria because it felt watered down. The waiter that we had was suggestive and didn&#39;t miss a T with us. <br><br>Overall it was a great initial experience there and I&#39;m excited to go back on the nicer days so I can wear my sunglasses and sit outside too.",
