"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This is my favorite restaurant in the city. My girlfriend is vegan, so this place is the best of both worlds for us. There are quite a few options for her and they are noted as vegan on the menu. She almost always gets the Shanghai Noodles.<br><br>I&#39;ve had just about everything on the menu. Zero complaints. The porchetta is freaking perfect. The lamb belly stir fry is one of the finest meals I&#39;ve ever had. Pork buns, scallion pancakes, homemade pickled veggies. chicken and waffles... I could go on forever.<br><br>The service has been excellent every time we&#39;ve been.  The waitstaff is always attentive to my girlfriend&#39;s dietary needs and I&#39;ve never had to wait around for someone to come to the table.<br><br>I don&#39;t drink but their homemade sodas are delicious. I highly recommend the cherry ginger and the lychee vanilla sodas. My better half ALWAYS gets the Bloodlust: a blood orange margarita with a sriracha salt rim. She&#39;s pretty picky but I know this is a cocktail she truly looks forward to.<br><br>DON&#39;T SKIP DESSERT. The french press coffee is strong and smooth. I usually get the coconut cream pie with homemade lime whipped cream. I&#39;ve also had the chocolate mousse with sesame brittle and tamarind caramel. it&#39;s vegan. It&#39;s decadent. It&#39;s awesome.<br><br>All in all, I can&#39;t say enough about this place. We&#39;ve had a couple less than memorable takeout experiences, but that doesn&#39;t take anything away from my love of Myers &amp; Chang. A+.",
