"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/bek0EgeTGlnQPA42XPYnqQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"When my good friend first moved to Somerville, I came down to visit for a weekend and after a night of pretty raucous behavior he suggested hitting up Sound Bites for a good post-debauchery breakfast. This was about 4 years ago and ever since this first experience, I have demanded that anytime I visit, we go to Sound Bites. The wait might look intimidating from the street but the amazing staff gets the tables turned over quick without making anyone feel rushed to leave. The menu is INSANE! So many selections and options. The coffee/iced coffee bar is genius and offers up so many different flavors. With a visit this weekend (first one in over a year) I felt compelled to write a review because I met the owner after he overheard me saying how amazing his restaurant is. He was warm and welcoming and even bought my friend and I a mimosa just for being there. I got their corned beef hash omelette. The corned beef hash is the most legit thing I&#39;ve ever eaten. Big chunks of meat, and definitely not the garbage out of a can. Throw in a side of a corn muffin and hash browns, with an amazing dark iced coffee, I&#39;m in heaven. What really sets them apart is the hash browns. Rather than fry up a handful of pre breaded frozen potatoes, or some silly shredded potatoes, they take thickened mashed potatoes and form a cake which they season and grill on the flat top with butter. <br><br>Hands down, my favorite breakfast spot on earth. If you&#39;re in Somerville, check it out. Nothing else compares. Also, the meal I had on Sunday might just be my death row meal.",
