"reviewcomment":"I try not to pick favorites, but the question of &#34;what&#39;s your favorite restaurant?&#34; comes up so often that I felt I needed to choose. And I chose Picco. <br><br>I&#39;ve been here multiple times, consistently had amazing pizza (although varying levels of amazingness, to be sure), inconsistently good service, and generally a nice atmosphere. It does get crowded at peak times and they don&#39;t have a high turnover rate since its the type of restaurant where people linger and enjoy wine and dessert (ice cream!). Nice if you&#39;re at the table enjoying said wine or dessert, not so great when you&#39;ve been &#34;the next on the waitlist&#34; for an hour and no one has left the restaurant. <br><br>I tend to order the pizzas with seasonal toppings. The toppings are delicious, the crust is fantastic. Chewy in all the right places with just enough crisp and char on the outside. Beautiful. I don&#39;t have a favorite because the menu changes fairly often and I generally can&#39;t get the same pizza twice. But no complaints here, I&#39;ve yet to be disappointed. I&#39;ve split a small pizza with a friend and had ice cream after and it was enough, though I could have done with a little more pizza. I&#39;ve also split a large pizza with a friend and finished it, but had no room for ice cream :( <br><br>Get there early. <br>Have some wine or beer at the bar while you wait for your table. <br>Order whatever pizza sounds the most delicious to you.<br>Eat delicious pizza.<br>Eat delicious ice cream.<br>Leave happy.",
