"reviewcomment":"Went to Abe &amp; Louie&#39;&#39;s for brunch over the weekend. Sat outdoors because the weather was awesome. This was actually my first time coming here for brunch and it was pretty damn good.<br><br>Instead of having bread and butter, they had a little basket filled with croissants, muffins, and pastries. They all tasted great! We ordered the steak tartare as an appetizer and it came in this huge plate. I&#39;ve never seen this kind of display for tartare before. In addition to the bread and steak, it also came with a salad and a some extra sides such as onions, cheese, mustard, and capers. The tartare itself was good, but I&#39;ve had better.  After that, I had the Crab Cake Benedict. Everything about it was amazing, especially the home fries. <br><br>It also wasn&#39;t too expensive for the amount of food we had. About $60 for two people. Abe &amp; Louie&#39;s is also great in the evening for steaks =)",
