"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been here a couple times before but have never gotten their food, before last night. I had a double cheeseburger and a side salad, along with a Smuttynose Bouncy House IPA.<br><br>The burger looked very much like two frozen patties, cooked to oblivion, and slapped on a bun that was too large for the shrunken patties. Plus, a nice slice of processed cheese product on each side. It did taste better than it looked -- basically just a slightly classier fast food burger. <br><br>The side salad was a pretty substandard assembly of iceberg lettuce, sad tomatoes, strangely large chunks of carrot, green bell pepper, and strangely mild white onion. The three dressing options were Ranch, Creamy Peppercorn, and Italian. I had the Italian, which I&#39;m guessing was Kraft or the generic brand from their food supplier. Wasn&#39;t horrible but next time I&#39;ll just sacrifice the healthiness and opt for fries instead.<br><br>All that said, $5.50 for a double cheeseburger and side salad is a pretty damn good deal.<br><br>Their beer selection is pretty good but the waitress wasn&#39;t quite sure of what rotating taps were available that night. There are some great bottles available as well. My IPA was tasty and not too expensive. <br><br>I&#39;ll definitely be back for some cheap food and good beer, especially on a nice summer night on their patio.",
