"reviewcomment":"So, I have been living in Boston/Cambridge for over 6 years and never have had a decent meal in the infamous North End--until tonight!!<br><br>We begrudgingly trekked out to N. End at the request of an out of town visiting relative and boy were we surprised.   <br><br>Pomodoro blew away all of my expectations as the food and service were both excellent.<br><br>We got reservations and were seated on time in a nice cozy table next to the kitchen where the wafting of the various meals being prepared really got us excited.<br><br>Got calamari and a bottle of vino to start with followed by some main courses.<br><br>To our surprise and delight the server brought us out a clams and fennel dish, which we thought was being dropped off at the wrong table, but our server informed us that she decided to treat us to the dish--great!! She brought us out more bread to dip in the wonderful sauce/broth and were were stuffed before our main courses even arrived.<br><br>For our mains we got the salmon, veal and chicken pomodoro--all were excellent.<br><br>Now that we were thoroughly stuffed and had stand up to stretch we were treated further by some free dessert--tiramasu!! <br><br>Suffice to say we left not only satisfied and stuffed but very pleased as we had a great meal which was quality at a very fair price.  <br><br>I would highly recommend this establishment as their wonderful service and excellent food will not disappoint.  <br><br>And yes if you are wondering if this review is 5 stars due to the free dishes we got--no as I would recommend this establishment despite those added bonuses.",
