"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Henrietta&#39;s is 4 stars for Sunday brunch and 3 stars for dinner! Because brunch is the most important meal, my weighted average ranking rounds to 4 stars. Chef Davis also gets bonus points for his commitment to farm-to-table fine dining!<br><br>Love it:<br>- Sunday brunch at Henrietta&#39;s is an experience that should be mandatory for all Cambridge foodies. The beautiful display of local goodness is enough reason to go. Highlights include the eggs benedict and amazing dessert options. Come with an empty stomach and a workout scheduled for the next day!<br>- Local cheese selections make for a great start to dinner.  <br><br>Like it:<br>- The entrees (salmon, steak, duck, and crab cakes at our table) were all simple and solid dishes. I just wouldn&#39;t crave any of them enough to die to come back for dinner!<br>- Chocolate bread pudding sundae and sticky toffee desserts were both good and impossible to stop eating, but again they weren&#39;t &#34;out of this world&#34; good. And let&#39;s face it, it&#39;s hard to make a dessert I wouldn&#39;t enjoy (at least a little). <br><br>Hate it:<br>- Service is fine, but not great. The waiters don&#39;t seem to share the same passion for local food as the chef!",
