"reviewcomment":"This is my favorite affordable sushi place to eat at--for what you pay, the quality is excellent. I would ignore the reviews complaining about the rice; sushi rice is supposed to be short grain, and my sister, who&#39;s lived in Japan for years, said Genki Ya has amazing sushi rice. However, if that&#39;s not your personal preference, then Genki Ya isn&#39;t for you.<br>The restaurant&#39;s a cute little nook and emphasizes organic food. My personal favorites are the rich salmon roll/salmon sashimi, and the genki ichiban. Their curry is good too!<br>But, most often, I order delivery. Since we live locally it arrives within an hour (I just plan the meal around that time frame for Brookline deliveries. Not sure about other places), and the sushi and miso soup are always fresh and delicious. Plus, when you order online, after a few orders you get $10 off. Always a great deal for me!",
