"reviewcomment":"Absolutely amazing food, I take all of my out-of-towners here. I spend the day raving about the Italian explosion they&#39;re about to have and they&#39;re never disappointed. The prices are so much better than the restaurants in the area -- think $15-22 max! The portions are gigantic, I always find myself taking home extras so that I can unabashedly enjoy them for lunch the next day. <br><br>I always stay with the Baked Ziti (with fra diavlo sauce) but the boyfriend has tried almost all of the pasta dishes. His favorite has to be the Linguine Pescatore -- I even like it, and I hate seafood. I always caution to eat the amazing Calamari because it really fills you up. The pasta is perfection and every bite is like a taste bud party.<br><br>The wait is always an issue but we try to circumvent this by making reservations (Yelp is your friend), however, even with a reservation, expect to wait at most 15-20 minutes to sit down. (Without a reservation...expect to wait awhile.) The place is extremely small (homey), but everything is worth it! The service is always excellent. I tell everyone that my absolutely favorite Italian food place (in the world) is Panza. (And you can always stare at the hungry Giacomo line across the street over your steaming dish of Baked Ziti.)",
