"reviewcomment":"Ok, I&#39;ve been here twice now and feel I can appropriately say this is one of my favorite pizza places in life. (FYI close rivals would likely be Cheeseboard in Berkeley, CA and Lombardi&#39;s in New York) If you are a fan of thin crust pizza, you will not be disappointed. I&#39;ve only ever tried their salads and pizzas so can&#39;t say much about the other menu options. <br><br>My friend and I always do a Greek salad with a 1/2 and 1/2 pizza, and we always end up leaving 2-3 slices behind b/c we are so stuffed! I would highly recommend the Portabello with Truffle Oil (absolutely divine) and the Fig with Prosciutto. Have also tried the Spicy Chicken Sausage as well as the Shredded Chicken with Gruyere. Both are excellent choices if you&#39;re looking for something with a little more protein. The pizzas have a nice crispy crust, but are also piled with toppings. Don&#39;t expect a crispy flatbread-like pizza -- this is the real loaded deal!<br><br>The restaurant is very small with no reservations so make sure you get here early or go on a weekday. Service has always been very attentive, and I always love getting a glass (or two) of the Sangria or red wine. Perfect place to catch up with friends, and who doesn&#39;t love the cute Beacon Hill neighborhood? The delicious tiny garlic bread cubes they serve at the beginning is always a nice plus as well.<br><br>I will definitely be back so I can try alllll the flavors. Must eat them all!!",
