"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"My whole family loves the lump crab cakes and clam chowder at Legal Sea Foods, so we really enjoyed coming to Legal Test Kitchen and getting what we loved with a spin on it.<br><br>What I love about Legal&#39;s crab cakes is that it is just straight-up lump crab meat with minimal filler--it&#39;s just delicious, honest-to-goodness crab! At Legal Test Kitchen, they serve this same crab cake (I asked to make sure) on an open faced sandwich with a fried egg on top--I love when things are served with an egg on top! It sits on a slightly toasted bun and is surrounded by various greens and asparagus and pancetta and the salad is dressed lightly with lemon. (I asked for the lemon aioli on the side). Two thumbs up for a new take on my Legal go-to dish!<br><br>The staff were friendly and helpful and we had such a lovely Mother&#39;s Day lunch here. I also found the menu to be much more exciting and interesting than the one at Legal Sea Foods and will definitely be back to try some of the other dishes that had also caught my eye!",
