"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/43IO63gALEVx6ooer0mGpQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"What is there to say other than... eh. I work in the Pru so this is a super convenient lunch spot for me that is typically pretty quick - they get you in and out in a timely manner. Our server, Ben, was great. He was quick to approach the table and often checked in to see how we were doing. <br><br>My friend and I both ordered burgers - both Medium Rare. The burgers appeared to be more on the medium side, but as long as they&#39;re not an overdone brick then I&#39;m okay with it. My friend got the Original burger which came with a heaping glop of rosemary aioli. The amount of sauce that was on the burger was gross. Really gross. But easily removed which doesn&#39;t make it too terribly offensive. <br><br>I had the avocado ranch burger which came with the perfect portion of avocado and just a hint of ranch - great in my books! As mentioned, I ordered my burger medium rare, but it appeared to be more on the medium side. The burger was okay and the sweet potato fries were really hot and crispy - yum! <br><br>The only thing that annoyed me was the server that appeared at our table when my friend was struggling with the ketchup. It wasn&#39;t our server, but the man found it would be helpful to teach her how to correctly pour ketchup from the bottle. I get it. It&#39;s a kind gesture. But this guy would not go away. And after going on his rant about how to correctly pour ketchup out of the bottle he appeared yet again with another method. Ugh. <br><br>Overall, the experience was okay. Nothing to run home and tell Mom about, but since this place is just so convenient to where I work it will always be taken into consideration for a lunch spot with friends or colleagues. Would I go out of my way to go here? No. There are other burger joints and even pubs in town that have much better burgers than what was served.",
