"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This place was a pleasant surprise for me. I went with a group of 7 people on a Saturday night. The restaurant was busy, but not overly crowded. The menu is part French part Cambodian. Rather than mixing the cuisines, the menu seemed to clearly delineate the plates from each region. Our tables was downstairs, and the vibe below deck was much clubier/swankier than above. <br><br>To start, I had the Soupe Phnom-Penh, which had noodles, pork, sprouts, and scallions. Salty and delicious, but not the most original dish in the world. That said, a few friends also ordered soup and mine looked the best. For my main, I ordered the Avocat Kanthor, which the waiter recommended. It was a smaller salad and was a little light on the greens, but the mix of raw tuna and avocado in the middle more than made up for it. Overall very tasty, but I&#39;d recommend ordering this as an appetizer because the portion size is rather small. <br><br>The waiter was friendly and attentive. The place had a fun atmosphere. We were able to get a reservation for a large party on a Saturday night with minimal advance notice. Definitely recommend this place.",
