"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I went here with two friends about two weeks ago for Dine Out Boston, and I loved it.<br><br>The service is impeccable. Our waiter was GREAT. He was very attentive, funny, engaging and knowledgeable (Not that it matters, but he was also super cute hehe) <br><br>We started with the Pate of Rabbit and the Venison Loin on the Dine Out Boston menu, but we also added some mussels off the regular menu. The mussels and loin were great, but my fav was the rabbit. <br><br>For our mains, we shared the Asian Spiced Duck Breast and the Pork Three Ways from the Dine Out Boston menu and added the Lamb Osso Buco. Everything was pure heaven. <br><br>The drinks were top-notch as well. I can&#39;t recall the name, but I had a spicy gin martini, per our waiter&#39;s suggestion, that was everything I wanted in a drink. <br><br>Also, the music playlist was so much fun. Michael Jackson came on and even the waiters couldn&#39;t stop themselves from dancing. It was such a great vibe. <br><br>At the end of our mains, they surprised our table with some chocolate fondue and fruit, and it was the perfect end to the night. We were all 100% satisfied. <br><br>Living about a 10 minute walk from Temple Bar, I know I will be back very soon. :)",
