"reviewcomment":"My friend and I sat at the bar, so I don&#39;t have much of a review for service (we were catching up and watching the Bruins game so if anything took longer than expected, I didn&#39;t notice). <br><br>Atmosphere: 5 stars! I love how it is completely open to the seaport, but still provides the safety from unpredictable northeastern weather. I also love the set up and decor. Definitely could be a nice date spot.<br><br>Food: Overall, I thought the food was very good. My friend and I split the lobster guacamole and short rib tamale. I like that they gave us a good amount of chips - it really bugs me when you order a $$ guacamole and have to keep asking for more chips. If you love lobster and love guacamole you can&#39;t go wrong. The food wasn&#39;t amazing my any means, but good size portions for what you spend. I do think they should sell the tacos separate instead of requiring an entire entree size. I now live in DC and that&#39;s how every taco-selling restaurant I have been to does things down there. No one really wants to eat rice and beans when you&#39;re out for a drink and need just a little solid food in your stomach...<br><br>Drinks: Good - not amazing. I had the Besos. It wasn&#39;t too sweet and I love basil in my cocktails, but it had too much crushed ice.",
