"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/zcRCbpLzhDIYtguEtqHJUw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I recently moved back to Somerville and we decided to grab dinner at Johnny&#39;s the night of the move. Just as good as I remember! Interesting crowd, fun and down to earth staff, and solid food.<br><br>My Nina Panina was awesome: lots of fresh mozzarella, lots of delicious basil, and thank god it wasn&#39;t drowned in balsamic. They serve the sandwich on sourdough, which was a neat twist that really works. Boyfriend reports the cheeseburger (local grassfed beef!) was very satisfying.<br><br>The peach blossom drink they were serving was likewise awesome: very refreshing, made with tequila, peach schnapps, and lime. I was a bit afraid it would be a sugary mess,  but the tequila gives it nice smokiness, and they add grapefruit juice so it&#39;s a tart, tangy drink great for warmer weather. Nice selection of local &amp; not-so-local beers, too.<br><br>I was concerned we wouldn&#39;t be able to grab dinner because they were having a show, but it was no problem. Will definitely be back!",
