"reviewcomment":"If you are not aware this place is right on the pier where the fish is brought back to the warehouse. Rad location. This place is nothing fancy, you should base your review as an overall out of 5 for what the place is, and what they advertise themselves to be. Being on the pier the fish is obviously some of the freshest fish you will eat in your life. <br><br>We sat by the window. Rad building nearing a hundred years, well built which is something I dig. Watched fishermen getting back from their shift throw scrapes to seagulls. Being from the the Rocky&#39;s that alone was worth the seat.<br><br>The fish could have been from a few hours old, to at most a couple days. Fantastic! The scallops are like candy. I got the assorted fried plate. If I return there while I am in Boston, which is likely, I will get a broiled plate to avoid the inevitable nap afterwards (errr maybe that was more the red eye plane ride?) Huge portions. I enjoyed the pickled relish that came with it. Some might prefer tarter, so request that. <br><br>Received a 4 because I did think it was a little expensive for what I received. Although the seafood was more fresh that anything in town, you are paying for the location. Which is a pretty rad spot honestly. I&#39;m kind &#34;snob&#34;, shop at Whole Food&#39;s, try to eat the most natural food I can when I can and this was not that. But it obviously was a diner, and I knew that before I arrived. I went because of where it is and how fresh the fish was. Life is too short to not put aside your ideals from time-to-time, especially on vacation.<br><br>If you are from out of town, especially inland like me, I highly suggest coming here if it is not too far out of your way. The view, fresh fish, and rad old building alone is worth the stop. Cheers!",
