"reviewcomment":"The funky interior and soft lighting make this a great spot for couples, but the lively atmosphere also is great for groups of family or friends (maybe not for a business meeting). The menu features mostly small bites broken into three categories (tacos, a la plancha, and small bites) with only about 4 entree options.<br>Three of us dined here and decided to go for round after round (after round after round) of nibbles. It was fantastic. the fried Manchago was to die for, the pork belly plancha was melt in your mouth and the seafood tacos were other worldly. We tried about 18 plates (pigs we were!) and all were good or above (not everything is a hit).<br>Cocktails were OK, with the blood orange margarita winning us over (pitcher 36 bucks give you 5 pours)<br>Service was a bit much...the server only had one or two tables and kinda hovered around us too much. I like an attentive server, but one who is standing next to me for 1/3 of the meal is a bit much.<br>The only down side is that it adds up, and quickly. figure $100 per head to nibble and sip like we did...then add the tip.",
