"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Came with a large group of friends on a random Thurs night and we were seated promptly. Since we were a large party 4-5 people used one pot to cook, but that was fun. We went with a miso soup base and a regular soup base. This place is pretty big so I think they can accommodate large parties easily.<br><br>I ordered the beef and seafood combo and it was a lot of food! It was fun teaching some of my non-Asian friends how to cook hot pot and watch them eat. <br><br>They had ponzu sauce, satay sauce, chopped green onions, chopped garlic, and  chopped chili peppers for your sauce. It def helped gave the meat some extra taste. The soup base were a little bland, but the other pot ordered a spicy thai base and that was really good. I think the portion for the combo was just right, but some of the guys said they still felt hungry after we finished all the food. <br><br>The veggie plate was ok... felt like it could have used a tad more veggies. The amount of seafood and meat was perfect tho. And I got some noodles that I cooked at the very end. Very satisfying! <br><br>They also have a red bean soup as dessert and that was pretty delicious! Oh, and they had fresh watermelon juice and that was really refreshing too!",
