"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"I am starting with dessert because a dessert here has made my top 10 list... and I couldn&#39;t believe it as it did NOT involve chocolate. I got the floating island as I was curious because of the name, and the waiter told us it sells out quickly every night. I got the second to last one. Now, I have never ever liked meringue. I dislike it very much, but figured I would try it at a french place. My god. The first bite was heaven. Melt in your mouth goodness. I am not ashamed to say I ate the entire thing. It was far to good to leave on my plate and very light for a dessert. Perfect ending to a perfect meal. <br><br>I had oysters for starter, not the best I ever had.. but clean, fresh, cold and the martini was delicious that I ordered with it. <br><br>For dinner I had the duck confit that everyone is raving about on this page. You all were right. It was perfectly cooked duck and the flavor they brought out with the light sauce was outstanding. I had to keep giving my husband bites to continue to agree with me how good it was. <br><br>The staff was very friendly, atmosphere pretty. I would have liked tables for seats to be a little closer. I felt like my hubs was miles away. Get some romantic tables for two added :)",
