"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/R20ktK7v1_XipCie8o8Nag/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Great patio seating especially on a nice sunny day for lunch!<br><br>Went here on the suggestion of a coworker.  I will say if you don&#39;t have &#34;your spot&#34; in the North End it can be a bit overwhelming trying to find a nice place.  <br><br>Well this is one I would suggest.  <br>We started with an appetizer of fried calamari.  While we waited for that we munched on the amazing bread and oil.  Simple, but fresh.  Nothing worse than old bread at an Italian joint.  NOT the case here. <br><br>The fried calamari... Amazing.  I could have had a plate of that on my own for my meal.  We are self proclaimed calamari connoisseurs, purely off of the fact I have had so many that are gross and unappealing.  This was lightly fried to the point when you stab them with a fork the batter flakes off... Perfection.  And, they know how to season their food.  So tired of bland food from restaurants.  And the sauce was so good I asked for more bread and dipped that in there too. <br><br>I ordered the salmon and zucchini with pasta and a white sauce.  Good...  The salmon pieces were small and the sauce was a little under seasoned but it was good.  <br><br>My coworker got the Pollo Lemón. It looked great, I do wish I had given that a shot, but it was just chicken no broccoli or spinach which would have been nice.  I think it was actually supposed to have pasta, but he choose not to so that could have evened it out a bit.  <br><br>Over all a great spot...  Now just to go back and have some drinks as well when I&#39;m not working.  <br><br>Try it out and you won&#39;t regret it!<br>Good luck foodies!",
