"reviewcomment":"Why I&#39;ll go back:  Mexican food that stands out as being high quality, authentic, and meticulously prepared.<br>You HAVE to order:  The chilapitas - a complex combination of plantains, pulled pork, and several toppings that add flavor and zest to this app<br>Tony&#39;s Tip:  Between the music and chatter from other diners, it can get loud in there.  If that&#39;s not your thing, try going for lunch or on the early side of dinner.<br><br>Zocalo is my go-to Mexican restaurant in Boston.  Yes - better than Temazcal, better than Papagayo, better than Casa Romero.  There&#39;s a plethora of choices across the salad, appetiizer, small plate, and entree sections of the menu.  And the guacamole is the best I&#39;ve had in the city - it is prepared with a little more lime juice than is typical, which enhances the inherent blandness of avocados.  Service is competent and friendly.  Getting a table as a walk-in is hit or miss, so I&#39;d suggest making a reservation just to be safe.",
