"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been craving hot &amp; sour soup for days, but was leery about venturing out and getting some since most of my Boston adventures in Asian food have been disappointing. I ended up ordering hot &amp; sour soup and pork eggplant on grubhub from Golden Temple around 11:15 am on Sunday. Not expecting it until closer to 1 I was pleasantly surprised and a little flustered when the delivery guy buzzed me at 11:50!<br><br>The hot &amp; sour soup was definitely darker and thicker than what I&#39;m used to in my hometown (Honolulu), but was hot &amp; sour and hit the spot. The pork eggplant was pretty also not the best I&#39;ve ever had - the pork had crunchy bits and there were red bell peppers in it - but the sauce was good and the scallions added a nice flavor.<br><br>Overall, it was A-OK with an added star for prompt delivery on a cold, January morning in Boston and the super nice delivery guy who actually APOLOGIZED for being early (no need to apologize! I was just surprised!).",
