"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Punjab is probably the best Indian in the Arlington Center area.  Lately, it has become my goto place for takeout after a late-night class as Tufts or just when there&#39;s no energy to cook.  I&#39;ve tried several selections from each of the menu&#39;s main sections, i.e. Hot Appetizers, Cold Appetizers, Classic Curries, Favorites, Tandoori, Biryani, and Vegetarian.  Part of this sampling was deliberate and part was involuntary as about 50% of the time, what I&#39;ve ordered is not what&#39;s in the bag.  So you could, as I often do, view this as a blessing in disguise, an opportunity to sample some dishes you normally wouldn&#39;t think to try.  It&#39;s only a real drag when a selection is completely omitted and not substituted for another. I will say that the folks at Punjab always make amends, giving the desired selection without a fuss plus a few extras for the inconvenience of having to return (which sometimes is the next day for me!).<br>A few comments on the food are in order.  Nearly all selections are excellent with my favorites being: Homestyle Chicken Curry, Tandoori Chicken, Shrimp Biryani, Rogan Josh, Aloo Gobhi, and Saag Paneer. What doesn&#39;t work so well are the Tandoori Lamb or Biryani Lamb which is consistently and completely overcooked to a withering end.  Bainghan Bhartha seems overly oily.<br><br>All in all my favorite Indian place north of Desi Dhaba in Central Sq.",
