"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Boston Chowda is in the middle of the Faneuil Hall food court tourist trap, but that doesn&#39;t mean it&#39;s not worth trying.<br><br>For $16.95 you can get a sandwich combo that includes a small clam chowder or other soup of your choice along with an amply stuffed lobster salad roll in a grilled 8&#34; bun and a small soda.  A perfect New England seafood binge when you are on the run around Boston proper.<br><br>The chowder is quite good and is not overly thick and heavy.  It has plenty of clams and potatoes that make for a nice balance. <br><br>The lobster roll has plenty of tender meat.  Salad style is never my first choice for these rolls.  Hot butter style is always best but, in a pinch, this will more than suffice.<br><br>You can also get their chowders and bisques in bread bowls if you aren&#39;t feeling the lobster roll, among a host of other seafood choices.<br><br>I must admit I was skeptical prior to trying this spot thinking &#34;tourist rip-off&#34; but I came away impressed.<br><br>The food looks tempting as you walk by and actually tastes as good as it looks.  You can&#39;t go wrong with that recipe.",
