"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ROO-UsfE58XuTU5vePWPiQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"We were looking for something different in the city (and outskirts!) of Boston that would really titillate our tastebuds. A coworker that worked with the boyfriend suggested that we try this place. Actually.... I think she suggested the grasshopper tacos but we shied away from that (even thought they reportedly taste like shrimp... and I like shrimp... in fact I ordered a shrimp entree!). <br><br>The food here is supposedly &#34;real&#34; Mexican food. I&#39;d believe it. This was definitely not your tex mex at your local taco bell. We started off the night with a plate of mixed tamales. Awesome... there were both sweet and savory with different types of ingredients tied neatly into little pouches like they were gifts for us. <br><br>Our entrees included a shrimp (sorry don&#39;t remember the name and it&#39;s not listed on their online menu!) dish that was covered in a green peppery, lemony sauce with a deliciously seasoned rice and bistec borracha which was steak in a beautiful marinade/sauce. Have you seen walking dead? What am I saying, of course you have. Well when I started tasting the food, I felt my primal instincts taking over and I just wanted all that food in my mouth... kinda like those hangry dead.<br><br>Now that your appetite is ruined after I mentioned zombies, we went onto dessert. The meals were a perfect size not making you overly full but not leaving you dissatisfied (although I wouldn&#39;t have minded being overly full). We decided to give dessert a try and on the menu the avocado cheesecake looked like something that wanted to get devoured. It&#39;s a dessert that wasn&#39;t overly sweet but you can definitely taste the avocado and definitely taste the cheesecake ;)<br><br>Parking&#39;s kind a @#$%. I am surprised at how few people there were at this restaurant. I invite you all to go. This place is a MUST if you&#39;re in the area.",
