"reviewcomment":"I went to Thailand 2 years ago and came back with such strong Thai food cravings all the time! There are a handful of good Thai restaurants that I frequent, but I really wanted to seek out that one super authentic hole in the wall that would remind me of the Thai street food that we had (while probably not the best idea at the time, luckily all of our stomachs survived). <br><br>Found S&amp;I on Yelp and was amazed by all of its reviews of authenticity. Tried them, and they really are all that jazz. While it&#39;s super hard to veer away from the typical pad thai or pad see you (because they&#39;re freakin delish!), you really should. I totally recommend trying something different from the &#34;Authentic&#34; part of the menu. I did today, and am blown away. Don&#39;t even remember the name of what I ordered (I&#39;ll update this when I do, but it was the last dish from the Authentic column). It was a flat noodle soup with pork blood, liver and intestines. The soup is savory, with a slight tang to it. It also has tofu and these deep fried pieces of skin that are so so yums. I typically really enjoy (read: LOVE OMG freakin love) pork blood from Vietnamese cuisine, and I&#39;m not sure if it&#39;s the difference in cuisine or not, but my one small gripe is that the texture of the pork blood is not good to me/what I&#39;m used to.",
