"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I cannot believe I have not reviewed this place yet! If you go to school across the river this is a must-go for a quick week night meal.<br><br>I pretty much loves anything I order here. The pizza is proper thin crust that still holds it&#39;s shape when you pick it up. The garlic bread sides are warm, cheesy and hearty. My go to is the Bolognese with homemade fusilli. The meat sauce perfectly coats every strand if the pasta, and after having homemade pasta it&#39;s so hard to go back to dry pasta! <br><br>The place is small so it could get crowded during dinner hours. Luckily they do takeouts. Also prepare to have lots of leftovers for the next day as the portion is huge! The only way I ever finished anything here is by sharing an entree with someone else. And even then I had to stuff myself.<br><br>The only downside of this place is it does not do delivery, and in cold winters I often dream about the place 10 mins down the road yet just did not have the courage to go out. Please consider delivery! You will have so many customers at HBS....",
