"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/YKe0HtNiw8Kz1VElrkgdpQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This place is awesome.  While I have never actually eaten at the Newbury St location (the one time we tried to get dessert there, we were turned away inexplicably) this is a  great offshoot of the original that is more of a neighborhood restaurant.<br><br>The staff is always friendly and accommodating (they have in the past served me the excellent chunky chicken salad that&#39;s not on the dinner menu for dinner).<br><br>Today was exceptional and I wanted to single out Cameron K. for his superb service!<br>He was pleasant, efficient, and every need was attended to, mostly without having to ask. Water refills, etc were all seamless. While this SHOULD be the norm ALL the time, we all know that is often not the case.<br><br>The food here is always good, including the cocktails which are well mixed and change regularly, and the somewhat famous Bloody Mary -- which comes with a check list of all sorts of ingredients to add (from bacon to olives to slim jims.)<br><br>The space is comfortable and nicely decorated, as well.<br><br>This is one of my go-to places, it&#39;s easy to forget how good it can be, but every time i go, i think &#34;why don&#39;t i come here more often.&#34; Isn&#39;t that what you want to say about a favorite neighborhood place?",
