"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/oKIMqAQDOvWEYB57BG1Adg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"The Orinoco in Brookline is like the Khloe to the South End&#39;s Kim - somewhat less popular, but very much from the same roots. Whereas the wait in the South End is inevitable, we were seated in this location right away, which is a big plus in my book.<br><br>After multiple visits to Orinoco, I have yet to go wrong with the menu. I highly recommend the maracuchitos (cheese-filled plantains) and the bacon-wrapped dates as appetizers. The empanadas are also fantastic, as is the pernil arepa.<br><br>My one nit with this place is that my friend&#39;s virgin margarita was a whopping $9, which is the same as any alcoholic beverage on their menu. Can you really justify charging that much when you just dump margarita mix in a salt-dipped glass and call it a day? The waiter&#39;s explanation was less than satisfactory - &#34;It&#39;s actually on the cheap end of our drink list.&#34; Maybe because it&#39;s not an actual drink?<br><br>Mini-rant over. Come here for the food. You&#39;ll have a great meal.",
