"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"So, I just learned that this place was here LAST week..despite living around the corner from it for a year. Glad I moved away to find it. Anyway, stopped in here last week with a few friends for dinner. There were 5 of us, but when we arrived there was only a table available right next to the door (it was kind of chilly out, and people were holding it wide open) Our waitress seated us and told us that she would move us as soon as another table became available..which she did. She even brought us our drinks and let us order our food while we were waiting. <br><br>I got the BLT with avocado, which was good..but I wasn&#39;t blown away by the bacon. It tasted like someone had poured an entire bottle of the &#34;smoke&#34; flavoring over it, due to the fact that it wasn&#39;t completely charred black. The rest of the sandwich was tasty, and they have a great beer selection. I loved the atmosphere, and the staff was friendly and helpful. I&#39;d try a different entree next time, but I&#39;ll totally be back!",
