"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I would do 3 for service and 4.5 for food. <br><br>I always have smoked salmon eggs benedict when I come here, and I keep coming back to this place for a reason. Eggs are perfectly poached, tomatoes are grilled just the right amount, the toast is well done too and their sauce is fantastic. On top of that, the potatoes are heaven. <br><br>I usually split the blintzes with someone as well. While good, I have definitely had a lot better. The cottage cheese in these is quite granular (while I remain a fan of creamy) but this surely is a matter of taste. Note that you have to order any fruits separately. <br><br>For the service, they are pushy. Particularly on Saturday and Sunday mornings, which is when I am guessing they see most of their business, they tend to give you the receipt before you are even done eating the main course (which is rude to begin with, but is particularly uncomfortable if you intended to order something else too). I get that there is a line for getting a table, but if people want to order more food the least you could do is ask whether they are finished before you shove the check on their table.",
