"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/NC4ljl1OfmYFSR37jla5bA/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Mary Chung&#39;s is a classic place in Central Sq that has been there forever and is an integral part of MIT/tech square history. It is not for everybody. You have to like spicy food and be prepared to put up with notoriously curt wait staff. The food and service is authentic Chinese, not Americanized Disney style Chinese. <br><br>Mary by the way is very friendly and is often at the register.<br><br>They are cash only, no credit cards accepted here. Don&#39;t forget to do an ATM run before dinner.<br><br>When I worked in Cambridge I used to eat here at least once a week.<br><br>They have a few classic dishes that are just awesome, in particular Suan La Chow Chow and Dun Dun Noodles with shredded chicken. <br><br>Their Dumplings are addictively good.<br><br>I also really like their Ma Pa Tofu. They use soft fresh tasting silken tofu which I love. (An earlier review incorrectly assumed it was not fully cooked.)<br><br>The rest of their menu is good, but not outstanding. Their Dim Sum on Sunday has a relatively limited selection.<br><br>Parking in central square is disaster, which is the main reason I don&#39;t visit Mary&#39;s more often when I am in Cambridge.",
