"reviewcomment":"I have to say, I was not expecting to give this place five stars. Don&#39;t get me wrong-- I love pizza, I love bowling, and I love the sort of low-key relaxed experience that the intersection of the two would imply. But I was basically expecting the emphasis of the place to be on the bowling, with the food as an afterthought. <br><br>Instead, I was treated to some truly spectacular pizza-- and let me reiterate, I *love* pizza. The first time I came to Flatbread Company I was with my work colleagues to celebrate a baby shower. We had one pizza with sausage and red peppers, and another with pepperoni. Both were perfect-- crispy, flavorful, with the perfect balance of sauce to toppings to crust. I was also charmed by their half pint beers. I love to try new beers but hate ordering a pint of something I might not love, but at around $2 per half pint, there&#39;s no reason not to get adventurous. <br><br>The next time I came back I was with a coworker and a friend. Our waitress was the same one who had served us at the party two weeks earlier, and she remembered us-- major points. We split the sausage and red pepper pizza (yep, it&#39;s that good) and one of their specials, which featured sage, butternut squash puree, and goat cheese. Who would even think to put that on a pizza? But it was amazing. And despite the abundance of families, small children, and the sounds of bowling everywhere, we didn&#39;t have to scream to be heard, nor did we feel like we were crashing a second grader&#39;s birthday party. <br><br>This was a great experience both times I went, and I will definitely be returning. Maybe beer and bowling don&#39;t go together so well-- I&#39;ll look forward to finding out.",
