"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/sLjuTxz61EyB3X1-cpKtsA/l.jpg",
"rating":"2.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve always heard that the &#34;center bar&#34; is much coveted in the business. I don&#39;t doubt that it is but it only works if the edges of said center bar don&#39;t extend out  to the establishment&#39;s walls. This place would be better served having a 3 sided bar extending off of the wall that is to the right upon entry. Once this place gets remotely crowded, you are in somebody&#39;s way 100% of the time because of the narrow corridors.<br><br>Over the years, the food here has been pretty standard bar food . If you are expecting something extraordinary, I don&#39;t know why you would go here instead of one of the dozens of extraordinary restaurants that sit within a mile radius of this joint. Joshua Tree is basically a place where friends who live in the area get stupid with friends who used to live in the area and are now visitors to the area. <br><br>A bulk of my visits to &#34;The Tree&#34; (just lost a bit of my soul) took place in my early to mid 20s which is now a decade ago but I have been in a handful of times in recent years with my buddies who will only go to really generic bars that have TVs every which way you look. The crowd really hasn&#39;t changed. From opening until about 8 it is a fairly reasonable crowd. After 8, at least Thursday through Saturday, a steady stream of frat and sorority D-listers pours in. In other words, if you&#39;re a broski or a puss faced little princess who can&#39;t have a good time, you&#39;ll fit right in. <br><br>The reason for my 3 star review is because the 3 star review on Yelp is basically meaningless. It doesn&#39;t really say anything. But, it somehow best describes Joshua Tree. There&#39;s nothing overly bad or good about this place. It&#39;s very typical. Everything is predictable. Somebody else mentioned that it&#39;s run by the same outfit that runs those taverns that are in squares and whatnot..... That doesn&#39;t surprise me. Those joints are the same: Plain, no real character, lotta football heads, decent nachos, etc.",
