"reviewcomment":"I don&#39;t even know where to begin, so I suppose I will go with the appetizers?  <br><br>We hosted our apres-nuptial dinner here and it was amazing.  Mamma Maria puts together a nice menu with plenty of choices and a nice selection of different items for each person to enjoy.  <br><br>The pesto... the polenta... the scallop... these were things that people were muttering, while looking down at the table, between bites.  The selections were perfect at an hour where one sort of needs an appetizer to keep them from devouring a large meal.<br><br>The salads were excellent, as is the wine glass that is magically never empty.  Our guests ordered a variety of different entrees and all were met with rave reviews.  All who ate the beef tenderloin in particular claimed it was the best they had ever had.  I ordered the cod and hadn&#39;t a clue that cod could be cooked so well.  <br><br>As if we hadn&#39;t eaten enough for an army, we had a cake to cut and the dessert platter coming out.  Oof.  I gained three pounds.<br><br>The service is amazing.  We ate dinner there in December and Jason was our waiter then, and we were both happy to see that he (and James) would be taking care of our wedding guests as well.  There is a very keen willingness to help, but they are also relatively soft-spoken, knowing when to interject and when to back away, which is becoming more and more rare these days.  Also, a few of our guests came with food restrictions that we hadn&#39;t known about, and they were accommodated quickly and with quality substitutions. <br><br>I have read many of the reviews for MM and all I can gather is that people want to complain about anything possible when their food is expensive, and that they may think they know more about the cuisine than they do, leading them to some degree of disappointment.  However, if you think to ask the staff to help you make your selections, I don&#39;t see how you could go wrong.<br><br>If you are looking for someplace to invest in a really lovely night out, or you want something different and more innovative out of the North End, or you want to plan a function with a little more class than normal, definitely, definitely, look into this little spot in North Square.",
