"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"I went here with my family and some family friends last night for a pre-Mother&#39;s day celebration. It was our first time at McCormick &amp; Schmick&#39;s. <br>We had a great waiter named Tim. Tim gave us excellent recommendations for different dishes on the menu. He was extremely interactive with us and he was great with the young kids we had with us. Our waiter was also extremely attentive. <br>The food was really good as well. My father ordered the shrimp scampi and praised that it was the best pasta he&#39;s ever eaten. I on the other hand ordered the Seared Ahi Tuna. The portions could have been bigger in my opinion but it was still delicious. My family also ordered two dozen clams and we chowed that down within minutes. They were so good and it was clear that the clams were fresh<br><br>However, there are a couple of things that prevents this place from getting five stars. 1) I called in a reservation for 7:30 yet when we got there we still had to wait an additional 15-20 minutes to be seated. <br>2) The food took awhile to come out as well. I mean we were with family friends so we didn&#39;t mind waiting too much, however I was starving by the time the food arrived at our table. We waited for about 40 minutes for our food to come out. To be fair, we did have a party of 8 though and everyone did get their food at the same time so that might be why our food was delayed. <br>3) The lighting of the restaurant made it hard to read the menu. The lighting is a minor detail but still, my sister had to rely on phone&#39;s light to read the menu!<br><br>Overall, we had a great dining experience with McCormick &amp; Schmicks. The service was fantastic and so was the food. My family and I will definitely be coming back.",
