"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I would highly recommend this restaurant.<br><br>FOOD - For my app I ordered the steak tartare, it was the perfect amount of saltiness with the potato chips. For my main dish  I had the Spice Rubbed Long Bone Rib Eye (lemon-parsley salad, bone marrow butter and harissa) 68. The rib eye was cooked perfectly medium rare. I finished the 24 oz - that&#39;s how good it was. It&#39;s very tender! For sides I ordered the truffled mac &amp; cheese, creamed spinach, duck fat roasted root vegetables, whipped potatos &amp; french fries. The vegetables &amp; mac &amp; cheese were AMAZING, a must order! <br><br>WINE: They have a promotion going on, for every 2 filet mignon &amp; bottle of Silver Oak 2009 Cabernet ordered, they will give you 1 complimentary filet mignon. We ordered two bottles and 4 filets, so we got 2 filets free which is a WIN! <br><br>SERVICE: The waiter was very personable, pleasant and attentive. We were a party of 10 and our wine glasses &amp; water never went empty.  He was very good with suggesting which sides to order and the right amount to order for the whole table. <br><br>SPECIAL OCCASIONS: We went for my boyfriend&#39;s birthday. They brought out the cake perfectly, sliced the cake and served it! They did not charge us for using their plates, some restaurants actually charge you $5 per plate for bringing your own cake.<br><br>Awesome night at Smith &amp; Wollensky, thank you!",
