"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/FmDbVZ9amIeKSOvkWWMP_g/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"This was my second time at TW Food. Took my lady for a weekend in Cambridge/Boston and knew i had to try their menu again. Once again we had the Grand Tasting with the wine pairing. They use seasonal and fresh ingredients here, so i wanted to see what the spring/summer menu would bring. So here goes: <br><br>1st: Creamed pea soup with bbq rabbit and mussels. It was a great way to start the meal. This was my lady&#39;s favorite dish of the night. The smokiness in the rabbit paired wonderfully with the light soup. <br><br>2nd: Scallop ceviche and seared scallops with sumac and Turkish spices. The ceviche was, in one word, amazing. A fresh burst of flavor that awakes the pallet for what&#39;s to come. This was tied for best dish of the meal for me. This was my girl&#39;s second favorite. <br><br>3rd: Foie Gras 3 ways. This was the other dish tied for 1st place. The seared Foie and the brule&#39;d were incredible. I wish i could have a steak sized Foie Gras. That&#39;s how good these were. For the 3rd dish, my girl had the gnocchetti, which was delicious. Very flavorful. BUT, i am so happy i went with the Foie Gras<br><br>4th: Lamb with mustard greens and morel mushrooms. Another great dish. The lamb was perfectly cooked and the morels were perfection. <br><br>5th: Cheese plate w/ fig jam and spicy almond. Wonderful cheeses that paired perfectly with the jam and almonds. <br><br>6th: Dessert. Fantastic. I don&#39;t remember exactly what we had, but i know there was brownie and graham cracker ice cream. <br><br>This dinner is in my top 5 easily, maybe top 3 meals ever. The wines pair wonderfully with the fresh ingredients used to compose the dishes. Service is friendly and attentive without being stuffy. TW Food is a place i have been to twice now, and they manage to wow me both times. If you are anywhere remotely close to this place, do yourself a favor and go eat there. You will thank me. ENJOY!!!!",
