"reviewcomment":"I don&#39;t remember to first time I ate at Kelly&#39;s Roast Beef, but I definitely remember my last - when I tried Roast Beast for the first time. I&#39;m hooked. I&#39;ve tried to think of a negative for this place, but got nothing. The only this I can think of is ...maybe...never being able to try to turkey because the roast beef is too delicious?  Yeah, I&#39;ll stick with that.<br><br>The first time I walked in I was a bit overwhelmed, but the staff is very helpful and wants you to get a sandwich you&#39;re going to love. The guy taking my order made some recommendations and even let me try some of the different cheeses and sauces they have. When eating roast beef, you gotta have horseradish...I go for the triple whammy - horseradish cheddar, raw horseradish, and horseradish sauce (I&#39;m a bit of an addict). For those of you who don&#39;t love the stuff as much as I do, I suggest mixing the beast sauce with the tiger sauce....add some grilled onions, lettuce, tomato, pickles...throw that all on a grilled onion roll and get ready for the best roast beef sandwich you&#39;ve ever had.",
