"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/KAfKO_XrLw4aYz7654CBBA/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I completely understand most people&#39;s reservations about this place - only one thing on the menu, so much food that your body hates you as you&#39;re walking out the door, unconventional seating and service. But I should clarify; I don&#39;t come here because of the gimmicks and quirky elements of the experience. I come here for the ramen. And believe me when I say that you should too.<br><br>This place serves, hands down, the best ramen I have ever had. I even spent a couple of weeks in Japan this past winter, and I&#39;d still like to say that Yume takes the cake. The innumerable ramen places in Boston and Cambridge cannot hold a candle to Yume when it comes to ramen. Most authentic ramen I have had in the US. I think the homemade noodles and fresh, fatty pork slices are the source of Yume&#39;s success. <br><br>Open late on most nights (11pm), however, their hours can be erratic (sometimes they can even be closed for several consecutive weeks if the owner is visiting family in Japan). I would recommend checking their calendar online before planning to go!",
