"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ubAYFNPc5MiSMVg8wbSl0Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been wanting to try Amsterdam Falafel Shop for a while now. I dragged my friend all the way out to Davis for a girl&#39;s date dinner, just to give it a go. And boy was it worth the half hour drive from JP. Can you guys open 10 more locations?<br><br>While the layout isn&#39;t so great (order...salad bar...pay...you can&#39;t linger there because there&#39;s always a big line of people, meaning you have to squeeze past the guests to grab your food), it&#39;s got a few tables to sit at. They will kick you out if you linger, which I can see getting annoying, but as it&#39;s such a popular place, people who want to sit and eat and very grateful. This isn&#39;t a snack you can stand and eat....these pitas are just STUFFED full of good things.<br><br>My friend and I ordered smalls (3 falafel balls) and french fries. The falafels were some of the best I&#39;ve ever had. Nice and hot, great texture, soft but crispy on the outside. And they tasted great. I topped mine with cucumber salad, beets, tzatiki, some parsley concoction, and some pickles. I picked up some dutch mayo, ketchup, and garlic sauce at the condiment station. That garlic sauce? TO DIE FOR. I slathered it on everything I could (including my face). Our french fries were very hot, salted and crispy, the best kind.<br><br>Great experience. Good service. They need to expand!",
