"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Wait, I haven&#39;t written a review on The Kinsale yet?! Shame on me, SHAME!<br><br>The Kinsale holds a very special place in my heart; it is where I had (evening) graduate class during my last two semester at Suffolk. The first keyword that comes to my mind is consistency. The food is always great, beer nice and chilled, and never a long wait to get a table (thanks to the deserted Government Center area at night).<br><br>Anyways, I had a little grad school reunion a few weeks ago. Let me set the scene - &#39;twas a chilly early spring day in Boston; rain was in the air and Bruins game on the television. As I awkwardly walked as fast as I can (is there anything more annoying than getting drops of rain on my glasses?!) I began getting some food cravings: french onion soup and veggie burger. I knew they had a damn good v-burger, so I was half-pre-satisfied. To my extreme surprise, they did have onion soup -- and it was the first thing on their menu! Perfecto! We also ordered a hummus plate to share. <br><br>The food is, as I said, consistent from time-to-time, which is really nice. I must say, though, it is nothing mind blowing, but it is a treat.<br><br>Pro tips:<br>1. The area once you walk in can get a little loud, especially if a Bruins or Sox game is on. There is a great and quieter section to the left! <br>2. They validate your parking if you park in the Government Center Garage (so don&#39;t be a fool and feed the meter and/or pay an expensive garage).",
