"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Great service, amazing sandwiches, questionable name ;)<br><br>The first time I heard of this place was from a friend. We were coming home from a booze-filled night and a friend suggested we grab brunch the next morning to stave off our (inevitable) hangovers. As brunch is my favorite meal, I enthusiastically agreed and asked where we&#39;d go. He suggested &#34;strip tease.&#34; I scoffed. There was absolutely no way I was going to go to a strip club for brunch! He assured me the food was out of this world. Riiiight, I said. Just like how guys go to Hooters for the wings? <br><br>Fast forward 2 years (2yrs ago). It&#39;s back on my radar. I finally figured out it was a play on words and that I worked just down the street! Co-workers and I come here all the time for lunch. Go early as it is always crowded and it&#39;s a tiny little joint. I&#39;ve tried almost all the sandwiches on the menu the past 2 yrs and you seriously can&#39;t go wrong. My favorite is their burger, although the specials are top notch as well. <br><br>Only issue is that this place is so tiny, and the benches/metal chairs are a bit uncomfy. Only other place similar to this is Parish on Boylston. If you&#39;re in Watertown, this is the best resto to check out!<br><br>Bonus: You get to tell people you&#39;re going to &#34;strip tease&#34; ;)",
