"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/X27httAwB3wCHWhPgH_w3A/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"All around good performance for this little neighborhood joint. <br>High marks for beer and wine selection and overall outstanding positive and professional service. <br>The food is very good not because it&#39;s unique but because they do simple things correctly. We ordered the buffalo pork belly, the smoked cod fritters, the lamb lollipops, the lamb sausage, the special flatbread pizza, the bison bolognese, and the manicotti. <br>Most of the things were conceptually very good but some were lacking in execution, bringing the star count down. Half of the pork belly was tough, the lamb sausage was overcooked slightly but not really enough to detract too much from the dish, but the manicotti was definitely something I&#39;ll be avoiding from now on...it was clumpy, tough, overcooked at parts and undercooked at others, and I don&#39;t know what the desired effect is for it but the kitchen definitely missed the mark.<br>The bison bolognese was excellent, the fritters were almost addictive,  the half of the pork belly that was cooked correctly was great, the lamb lollipops were perfectly trimmed, and the flatbread pizza was little more than a standard pizza with some good toppings but was executed very well, you can taste all the ingredients and it&#39;s not greasy or over-sauced. <br>Great ambiance and music too.<br>4.25 stars.",
