"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/bSOCdFvCesAlgeg7uljeBA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"There&#39;s a lot of &#34;grade inflation&#34; on Yelp.  Basically anything that doesn&#39;t suck gets 4 stars, anything that sucks only a little gets 3 stars, and 2-star establishments are probably some kind of dumpster fire.<br><br>I&#39;m happy to report that Shanghai Gate serves 5-star food.  Having grown up with a friend from Shanghai whose mother frequently prepared delicious dishes from her home city, I can say that Shanghai Gate is remarkably authentic.  Try the lion&#39;s head meatballs or the steamed pork with pickled vegetables.  I&#39;ve eaten here about a half dozen times now trying different dishes and I&#39;ve never left disappointed.  Oh and did I mention everything is reasonably priced?<br><br>The only catch is that the menu is littered with &#34;landmines&#34; consisting of generic Americanized Chinese dishes that you should avoid at all costs.  I&#39;m speaking of course about cheap Chinese take-out restaurant staples like General Tso&#39;s chicken, beef and broccoli, etc.  I mean, there&#39;s nothing wrong with any of these items per se, but why would you come to Shanghai Gate just to get an item that can be found practically anywhere else?  The gems are mixed in with the faux-Chinese duds, so you might want to ask the waitress for recommendations or simply glance around at other patrons&#39; tables to see what looks good.  It&#39;s a little tricky, I know, but the food is well worth it.",
