"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/-SgZrjwHDrsIGhQMw_-4xQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"For $3.50 a sandwich, only an idiot would go to McDonalds next door.<br><br>Popped by for a crispy accompaniment to a bowl of split pea soup at I had at home, and a pork banh mi sandwich fit the bill.  A no-frills storefront led to a no-frills order; my pork sandwich hit my hands one minute after I ordered.<br><br>Bread was spectacular, as was the taste blend with cilantro.  Meat quantity was a bit lacking compared to its Dorchester and food truck counterparts, but nonetheless very flavorful.  Even the tripe tasted good.  And the whole shebang was improved with my addition of sweet-and-spicy Maggi sauce (look for it at Indian markets).<br><br>Next time, will try the Vietnamese coffee with condensed milk.  Always a concentrated cup of flavor in its archetypal form, I noticed that these guys sourced coffee from New Orleans&#39; Cafe du Monde.  Interesting!",
