"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I know there are plenty of reviews here already, but I&#39;ve got to chime in!  The sandwiches are downright HUGE!! (and very tasty, too, I might add...very much like the old-time Jewish delis that were once so plentiful yet now impossible to find).  I&#39;ve ordered several &#34;half&#34; sandwiches here which are actually the size of a very abundantly-filled whole sandwich.  The hot dogs, or &#34;franks,&#34; as they are called here, are quite large and delicious, too!  You must come here with a healthy appetite as portions are very generous...an added plus for any restaurant, in my estimation.  I&#39;d also like to add that the people who work here are so friendly and and quite willing to help if you have any questions.  This is an important fact to me as I enjoy spending my money where the staff are considerate and congenial.  <br><br>The restaurant (a little storefront shop with a small amount of seating) is kept clean, but the decor, which is quite simple, could use a bit of refreshing or added zip.  Perhaps someday there will be more effort put into that aspect of the business. <br><br>Another thing I&#39;d like to add is this:  I think this deli is under new ownership, so anyone who had a problem with the previous owner (who I understand was rather rude), please give this place another try!  As they used to say on the old TV commercial, &#34;Try it, you&#39;ll like it&#34;!",
