"reviewcomment":"&#34;Oh Lord, may I be hungry and have about ten minutes to pop into Super 88 Food Court for a #37 at Pho Viet&#39;s whenever I pass the fork of Comm Ave and Brighton Ave.&#34;<br><br>What is a #37? Good question. The menu describes it as Dau Hu Xao Gung Com - Tofu Saute with ginger &amp; scallions with rice. The first awesome surprise is the large mound of rice they serve with it. Included. For about eight bucks you get a rectangular styrofoam carton packed with tofu to die for, incredible ginger sauce and other stuff. Seriously, I was trying to imagine camera angles so I could do savsana and get the restaurant logo into the picture to post to Ugly Yoga Postures to impress all my friends, over a hundred on Facebook alone!<br><br>Other stuff in the stryofoam carton includes about a head of broccoli, peppers, green and red, mushrooms, at least two kinds, baby corn, bok choy and who knows what else.<br><br>Once upon a time I was ambivalent about tofu. Not anymore! If money is no object get an order of fresh vegetarian spring rolls with the peanut sauce.<br><br>I love this place. Everything about it. It&#39;s fast, easy, cheap, a fun place to watch people, easy to park, T accessible, groovy friendly people at the counter and sriracha. Go there! Now.",
