"reviewcomment":"Two words: Dessert. Cart.<br><br>Instead of a dessert menu, at the end of your meal you will be presented with a dessert cart with 6 tantalizing dessert options, including a deep dish tiramisu that I will have to go back and try next time. I love dessert and I love being able to see exactly what my food will look like before I order it, so the dessert cart pretty much sealed the deal for me as the perfect way to end our delicious meal. Tip: Based on the two desserts we ordered, desserts appear to be $10 apiece. <br><br>The highlight of my night, aside from the sheer presence of a cart full of desserts, was the Lobster Bisque. I&#39;m not usually partial towards lobster bisques and I was getting lobster risotto for my entree, so I decided to pass on ordering any appetizer in order to save room for dessert at the end. However, after trying a sip of my dad&#39;s bisque, I was sold--dessert was just going to have to make room for this soup. It&#39;s a large portion and just the right balance of creamy and tomato-y with chunks of lobster happily adrift.<br><br>For my entree, I ordered the Lobster Risotto. One thing worth mentioning is that most of the lobster in the risotto, if not all, are all claw meat, including the rubbery pointy tips. It didn&#39;t necessarily detract from the risotto though. Again, it was a large portion and I ended up taking a small half of the risotto home with me. Their portion sizes are definitely one thing that sets them apart from other &#34;fancy food&#34; places.<br><br>My parents both ordered the Pan Seared Sea Scallops, which comes with 5 plump scallops sitting in a shallow pool of sweet creamy corn (which my dad replaced with grilled asparagus) and topped with a crunchy match stick potato garnish. The scallops were super tender and flavorful, yum! <br><br>Bonus stars for Davio&#39;s uncommonly extensive menu--this is definitely another thing that sets them apart. I generally find that expensive/fancy restaurants tend to have very short menus with only a handful of choices for each course, which is problematic because someone in my family often can&#39;t find anything on the menu that they really want to eat. This was definitely not a problem we ran into at Davio&#39;s and we all left with happy bellies.<br><br>All this being said, one of the things Davio&#39;s is known for is being a steakhouse, but none of us ordered any steak so I can&#39;t speak to that part of the Davio&#39;s experience.<br><br>I would definitely recommend Davio&#39;s if you&#39;re looking for a dressy night out in a elegant, spacious restaurant that can accommodate large parties and rocks a dessert cart.",
