"reviewcomment":"Ask my friend B.G. what is his absolute favorite restaurant in Boston, and he says Erbaluce, twice, in different emails. B.G. so far shares very similar taste in food with me, so I promptly made reservation prior to my trip to Boston. B.G. split time apparently between Boston and SF, like another friend of mine, come to think of it. If they are in fact uncanny double i would not be surprised. For appetizers: Dandelion greens and razor neck clams. For second course we had cavatelle with home made sausage. For entries: rack of wild boar and pork cheek. Fantastic bread with white bean dipping sauce, and to cap the evening truffles on the house.  French red to pair of course. <br><br>You would not think south end for Italian, at least for untrained eye such as I, but it was quite amazing. Every course was well executed, with lots of complex flavor profile, and the setting is sophisticated and even romantic (though was not my intent for the evening). There are many theatre goers heading out after, and there are many people waiting for tables on a raining night.  <br><br>For me the food is unique enough because you&#39;d not see this in San Francisco. Just not the same type of food really so the food felt a bit exotic, and thus more attractive to me<br><br>Afterwards, I wrote to B.G., &#34;You may not know this, but your friendship was hinged on your recommendation of a true great Boston restaurant. You did not fail. This time.&#34; <br><br>I have a handful more to try out from his list. But this restaurant definitely deserves a second visit, if not more.",
