"reviewcomment":"The best restaurant I have ever dined at with my boyfriend for my graduation dinner.<br>Most restaurants of this caliber tend to treat guests with less service if they don&#39;t order drinks. We both didn&#39;t order drinks because we both had a cold. Our server(s) still treated us as a valued guest and gave the utmost respect, which I really found important throughout my experience here.<br><br>We both ordered from the $95 prix fixe menu. There were tons of freebie bites in between!<br>What we got:<br><br>Hamachi (+)<br>Chilled Maine Lobster<br><br>East Coast Halibut<br>Faroe Island Salmon (++)<br><br>Berkshire Pork Belly (+)<br>Quail (++)<br><br>Baba au Rhum<br>Rhubarb Vacherin (Interesting...)<br><br>They also gave these for free:<br>caviar hamachi roll<br>savory macaron (goat cheese)<br>foie gras, jelly on crostini<br>Dark chocolate dessert bites<br>A bowl of macarons<br><br>Even though the entrees were small portions, the dishes were really savory and flavorful that we were beyond stuffed. We were too full to eat from the cheese cart. It looked amazing. <br><br>Overall, I had the best dining experience at Menton. They also got us a cab after our meal, and treated us with respect and the best service, even though we were the youngest guests in the restaurant and didn&#39;t order drinks.",
