"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"My boyfriend and I recently took a trip to Boston and we were advised to eat at the Chart House. The hotel had given us a map which had a coupon for a free appetizer (Chef&#39;s Special). They orignally sat us downstairs with no view of the water but we asked to be moved and they graciously moved us to the space upstairs. The place is huge! Our waiter was AMAZING! He was honestly the nicest man. He answered our questions about the city and made sure everything was ok, he was funny and very likable. <br><br>For an appetizer we had the Coconut Shrimp, which was on the house and delicious.<br><br>For the entree we both ordered Salmon, which was fresh and also very delicious. We were expecting small portions because that usually happens in places like this. The portions were very big, so you do get your moneys worth. <br><br>Our waiter was so good that he convinced us to get dessert which was a chocolate molten cake with vanilla ice-cream. I was so stuffed but this cake was so good that I couldn&#39;t stop eating it.<br><br>Everything was 5-star worthy! They should consider getting treadmills so people can run off the food after they eat. Although, the waiter did tell me I can run up and down the stairs a couple of times.",
