"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gzIxRWul1_j9XX3xQ1bTmA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"What a mind-blowing, tastebud-tantalizing experience! Came here after a day of shopping on Sunday. The space is huge and kind of reminds me of a Vegas restaurant in terms of the decor and exuberance. They do actually have a location in Vegas, as well as other parts of the U.S.<br><br>The salad bar has amazing choices, such as coconut haddock, pickled cherry peppers, thinly sliced prosciutto, cheeses, mango shrimp salad, etc. I almost got full just eating those!<br><br>The server also brings out complimentary sides before eating the meat, which include cheesey bread, fried polenta sprinkled with a salty cheese, garlic mashed potatoes, and caramelized bananas (not plantains sadly, but still good). These are unlimited by the way! :DDDDD<br><br>The meats come out in rounds and a lot of the time they will ask you if you are waiting for something in particular and they will get someone to bring it out for you in the next round.<br><br>My top meat choices:<br>-Linguica<br>-Filet mignon wrapped in bacon<br>-Sirloin<br><br>The organization, speediness, and friendliness of the staff was impeccable and unique to the sometimes poor service you get at other large chains.<br><br>The price was a bit pricey at around $55 per person, but for the variety and service you receive when dining here, it is worth every single penny. I actually can&#39;t wait to go back again. Have to try their different versions of Caipirinhas, too!",
