"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_oYg3jXVolmy7DQ6e_JMVA/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Based on the food-gasm-splosion that is TTR, I am completely redefining my rating algorithm. There&#39;s just no way that Tip Tap Room should be allowed to be in the same category as Tasty Burger (no offense, Tasty Burger, I still love you). It should be illegal, do you hear me? Goddamn illegal to even consider the possibility. I mean, based on my previous metric, Tip Tap Room should be rated about 10,000 stars. INFINITY STAR!!! I should start quoting Shakespeare now, like when Juliet waxes poetic about Romeo&#39;s face and how it&#39;s like all the stars in the sky or whatever. Bullshit! That wasn&#39;t Romeo&#39;s face, that was Tip Tap Room, son. <br><br>In this restaurant, literally everything single thing you can put in your mouth is insanely delicious. Including the cocktails, including the tablecloths, including the wait staff, should you charm your way into letting you lick their faces. These people are made of gumdrops and jelly beans. But. The best best BEST item on the menu is, in my humble opinion, the wild boar meatballs. Remember when I called ANYTHING ELSE amazeballs? I was wrong. THESE are AMAZE BALLS! These are literal, tangible amaze balls you can put in your mouth. And trust me, you will want these balls in your mouth. Since the menu is always changing, I would just recommend you skim through the entire thing and select what looks like the craziest, most unappetizing item. Order it, eat it, and I promise you won&#39;t regret it.<br><br>And wouldn&#39;t you know, the genius behind this glorious establishment, Brian Poe, is just about the most generous, dedicated, RIDICULOUS (in an awesome way) man you&#39;ll ever meet. Every night he drives around town and surveys his three restaurants, chatting with customers and just gushing all his food-love, which he has a LOT of. It&#39;s like his food-heart is 3x the size of a normal person&#39;s, and it&#39;s overflowing with passion for the culinary arts. If you get the chance, say hello, listen to him describe his recipes, take a ride in his jeep. He will probably offer you one. Just like the menu, it might sound crazy, but just go with it. Just go man. Just go.",
