"reviewcomment":"As we are nearing our move to New York, we started compiling our bucket list of restaurants we wanted to try. No foodies ourselves, we listened to our foodie friends and went to Clio.<br><br>We made our reservations online the week before, planning for the tasting menu. Unfortunately, because we each had to get up early and be functional the next morning, we opted against the wine pairing. Our made us regret this decision, and I think next time we will try the wine pairing. Instead we had the house cocktails, which although good, were not what inspired this 5 star review.<br><br>I don&#39;t want to go through all 14 courses, but notable items include the parsnip foam cassoulet with sea urchin and lobster. I didn&#39;t know such a thing existed! <br><br>I also never knew cod could taste so good. This was followed by seared foie gras and venison with bone marrow crust.<br><br>The waiter was both personable and knowledgeable.<br><br>In summary, I would recommend this to anyone willing to go on a culinary adventure.",
