"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Spicy curly fries.<br>YAY. &#39;Nuff said.<br><br>The Matador.<br>(hot-pressed panini with grilled chicken, sliced CHORIZO sausage, sautéed peppers and onions, cheddar cheese, &amp; kick&#39;n bayou sauce)<br>b. and I were sad when they took this off their panini list. So we were super excited when it reappeared recently on their specials. Curious, we asked the guy behind the counter why they had removed it in the first place. He said that it was because not that many people were ordering it (what?!) but since chorizo has become more popular lately (about damn time!), they put it back as a special. To keep it on there, he asked us to spread the word and tell people to order it more. So GO ORDER IT.<br><br>Wolf Man.<br>(monster burger with cheddar cheese, bacon, over-medium egg, &amp; sriracha mayo)<br>I only got this the one time and will probably not order it again anytime soon since I still want to live a little longer. I mainly wanted to include it in this review so to warn others. It was a good burger but damn, I thought I was going to keel over and die of a heart attack afterwards. I think it might have been the egg that was overkill for me since eggs can be fairly filling on their own. But sriracha mayo! YAY for sriracha!<br><br>The fourth star is purely for the service. Every time b. and I have been in, everyone has been friendly and helpful. There is one guy in particular (the one that was telling us to recruit more chorizo eaters) that is super friendly and welcoming. YAY.",
