"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/gd7Mk8OKmVgqljGHN7TV2A/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"This is one of our favorite Japanese Restaurants in Cambridge. We had dinner at  Blue Fin on Thursday evening. For those looking for sushi, this place offers the usual mix of sushi along with specials. For those looking for authentic Japanese food at a reasonable price, you ought to give this gem a try. We ordered three appetizers: a special - monk fish liver (fresh tako sunomono); nasu miso eggplant (nasu dengaku); spinach with bonito (ohitashi). All three were delicious. For entrees, we ordered the silver cod (gindara) and the Atka (hokke) mackerel. The gindara was marinated with miso and saki and was quite good. On the other hand the hokke was a bit on the dry side. The service was very good and prompt. Blue Fin updated the restaurant some years ago and aside from a few flat screen TVs and nice new menus, it doesn&#39;t appear much updating has been done since then. Overall a great dining experience.",
