"reviewcomment":"UGH James Gate...I want to visit you all the time! I live on the same street, and you&#39;d think I&#39;d go every day. This is not so. I made plans to meet my friend for an evening drink on Friday, and it was packed for the Bruin&#39;s game. We decided to sit in the dining room (there is a pub and a dining room, both with bars). I had a hard week at work, so I ordered a dark and stormy. It was pretty good, but nice and strong (just what I needed). My friend had a glass of wine, and she was excited to see how full it was (worth every penny).<br><br>So aside from a drink, I needed sweets...I got the flourless chocolate cake. It was a smaller portion than I had hoped, that being said, it was rich, and amazing. Who makes their desserts? It was a dome of chocolate (not too dense, but very rich), with a pool of chocolate and a mountain of whipped cream. My friend ordered it as soon as she saw mine. Copy cat.<br><br>I guess I can always pop in for dessert whenever I want (roll out of bed...show up at their door). I am ready to visit again!",
