"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I did not allow my girlfriend to help me write this review because she would get all sentimental about the waitress she made her best friend, so I will try and write an honest review in her stead.<br><br>Super Fusion is the best Sushi on this side of Japan. I cannot stress how fresh and amazing the fish is here. The only way to truly appreciate the quality and expertise of the sushi chefs is to get a seat at the bar and watch them do magic tricks with extremely sharp cutlery.<br><br>Everything I have ever got at Super Fusion my girlfriend describes as, &#34;the best ... ever.&#34; It is kind of like Richard Lewis coining, &#34;the blank from hell&#34; on curb your enthusiasm, but she uses the phrase A LOT at this spot. Normally I would tell her to stop overreacting and enjoy the melt in your mouth tuna, or the char grilled eel, but at Super Fusion, I have to agree with her. <br><br>I know there are fancier, larger, and more expensive sushi restaurants around the beacon street area, but it would be foolish to spend more money on an inferior product. <br><br>MY ADVICE: Go grab a six pack from around the corner (or some saki if your into it), take the short walk to super fusion, and make anybody fall in love with your expert taste in sushi hidden gems.",
