"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Great googly moogly this is the BEST italian restaurant in the Boston area. It&#39;s such a hidden jewel that the smithsonian should put it next to the hope diamond in their museum. Forget the north end. This place is in the back of a little deli/ grocery store. Just going there makes me feel like someone is &#34;going to make me an offer I can&#39;t refuse.&#34;<br><br>The apps were amazing and fast. I ordered the veal prime rib with pesto pasta. The meat was cooked perfectly. It was so tender, meaty and melt in your mouth I never wanted it to end. The pasta was perfectly al dente. The pesto sauce was well developed and seasoned. It was really fresh too, the basil hadn&#39;t even stopped growing yet. Anytime I get a craving for italian food, this is where I go. The food was so good I forget what the service is like. Dumbledore himself could have served it to me in his hat and gown, I still probably wouldn&#39;t have noticed. Writing this makes me want to go to there.....FYI the prices may seem high for a somerville restaurant...but I would gladly give my first born if I could be guaranteed a life time of dining options from this place. Alas the owner is not rumpilstilskin.",
