"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"Between 3.5-4<br><br>A couple of friends and I went here one night for margaritas as my friend works in Faneuil hall and the prices are right. We split the appetizer guacamole between the 2 of us. The molcajete it was served in is huge, thus the portion is very big. Oh and not to mention, the bottomless tortilla chip refills as well. As a seasoned guacamole taster, I feel confident saying the guac was delicious. I do prefer more cilantro in my guacamole, but in fairness, I have an unusual liking for cilantro and heavily cover a lot of my dishes at home in it. So, aside from liking more cilantro in my guacamole, it was really tasty. So tasty that my one friend and I polished off the whole serving with 3 chip refills :x  <br>From talking to the waiter, who is also one of  the managers, we learned that everything is made in house, from the taco seasoning mixes to the margarita mixes-big bonus! <br><br>We went to Zumas for the margaritas. Oh so tequila tasty. We each got the classic margaritas, not the Zumas classic, but the other classic. They were very good: strong and tangy! Just how they should be! <br><br>A couple of hours and margaritas later we were full, and feeling very good. <br><br>The service was fast and friendly. I will be back for some more",
