"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve lived around the corner from Hana for six years, and I never get tired of this place. I love sushi, and I&#39;ve been to all sorts of hi-test places, but Hana is tough to beat. I&#39;ve had friends visiting from manhattan tell me this place has ruined them for their own local sushi joint. <br><br>Don&#39;t expect anything revolutionary on the menu; it&#39;s mostly the standards. They just do them so, so well. The ingredients are excellent and they cut no corners. Even a basic spicy maguro roll arrives with a beautiful cut of tuna and just the right amount of bite. The speciality rolls are plenty dazzling though.<br><br>I may come here often, but it only took a couple of visits before they started treating me like their best customer. The owners know how to run a business. Jason, who is usually around, will often personally greet you when you step through the door. He might even deliver you a special treat now and again. <br><br>The rolls here are so good, you might never notice that they also have a small but excellent Korean menu. Turns out, you can get some of the best bibimbap here as well! Give it a shot!",
