"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/lB6Ed0qpWXtyoOBYkugbpQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"My experience at Mission Bar was much different than that of others who noted rude or inattentive service. I stopped in for dinner with my wife and son around 8:30 p.m. on a Thursday in late December. The place was packed with 20- and 30-somethings. There were only two open tables in different parts of the dining room, and they were two-tops. The manager could not have been more accommodating. He asked a party of 2 seated at a 4-top to slide over so we could be seated. He could easily have told us to wait or come back another time. Service from Ana was excellent. Did we just get lucky? Maybe. But I judge restaurants based only on personal experience. <br><br>The menu had much more than the usual pub fare, and I thought the prices were fine. My chicken saltimbocca ($16) was moist, well-seasoned with sage, and topped with fontina and prosciutto. My son&#39;s fish tacos ($16) were made with battered, deep fried cod loin. The fish flavor stood out rather than losing out to the batter and oil. The portion was small for the price. My wife&#39;s chopped salad ($12) was large and had a variety of ingredients. Draft Harpoon IPA at $5.75 was fresh and well-priced.<br><br>The energy in the pub was convivial. Everyone seemed to be having a good time. I liked the upscale, modern pub décor. We definitely will return. <br><br>Let me know what you think of this review by clicking a button below. Thanks.",
