"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/NkdfmHy6gUTizU5Y9czqeA/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"Note: This review is about the downstairs portion, only.<br><br>Up until recently, I had never actually eaten a meal here. Hello, people go to Scholar&#39;s to drink. It&#39;s a popular after-work spot for those who work in that part of town. The ambience is a bit upscale-ish, considering the neighborhood (the are surrounding the common can feel a bit sketch after dark, especially if you&#39;re closer to Washington Street). On a weekday, the place is packed with a slightly older, corporate crowd. On weekends, it turns into a top-40/college bar with a cover.<br><br>The bartenders are extremely attentive and friendly, and the drinks are strong. I usually stick to beer, but I have my go-to cocktail here, and it&#39;s the tequila smash. Tall, strong, and just what the doctor ordered after a crazy week. <br><br>As for the food, I get the same thing here every time, so I guess I can&#39;t give you a comprehensive review. The tuna tartare appetizer (which is really an entree size for one person) is amazing. Probably some of the best I have had. The tuna is fresh, and they serve it in three &#34;mounds,&#34; all different flavors and seasoning. There&#39;s the classic avocado, a lemon-basil, and the orange-sesame-ginger. The latter of the three is AMAZING--the Asian flare is fantastic. The other two are quite good, as well. This is served with lightly baked Pita triangles. I typically blow through the pita, and they always bring more out at no additional cost. <br><br>Table service can be a tad slow, so I zinged them a star. I usually stick to sitting at the bar, or in the couch seating towards the back of the room (if I am with a larger group).",
