"reviewcomment":"Head Line at this Hour: CITISIDE BAR AND GRILL CLOSED BY THE CITY OF BOSTON!<br><br>The owners of this Cleveland Circle landmark could not be reached for comment. <br><br>However, news of this action by the Boston Licensing Board comes as a shock to no one in the Brighton/Alston community! Citiside Bar and Grill was long infamous in the community for serving underage international students- some as young as 16 from the Japanese shoa school- with little or no regard for federal law or city statutes.<br><br>&#34;Yeah...I am really bummed this place is closed&#34; Said Sangmi J, an international student from South Korea and frequent underage visitor to Citiside Bar and Grill. &#34;It was Awesome. You just had to show anything written in a foreign language with your picture on it and the bouncers would just let you right it. I always just showed my (South Korean) High School ID card and told the bouncers that it was an Official Korean Govt Id saying I was over 21 and they would let me right in! And the Drinks there were really good and really cheap! I am so bummed out! Now I will have to go back to sneaking into the Estate club. Which totally sucks because I will be like the only Korean there and that is just like a total creep magnet to all the many creeper guys who lurk there! Damn! DAMN!!!&#34;<br><br>Also &#34;Bummed out&#34; is Brighton Resident Claude F. &#34;This is really disappointing&#34; Said Claude F. &#34;I used to come here about once a week for the Steak tips! They were Sooooo Good! And for under $20! You could not beat that! And they had great trivia events!&#34;<br><br>The question remains: Will Citiside re-open? And will it re-open with changed policies and perhaps no liquor license. We attempted to reach newly elected Mayor Marty Walsh for comment but he was too busy trying to get Sangmi J&#39;s phone number to give us any comment or any indication if Citiside will be allowed by the City of Boston to re-open or if the restaurant will now be yet another boarded up eye sore in the Brighton neighborhood. <br><br>Only time will tell. Stay Tuned!",
