"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/rPxjBKlWB4x5jcJB3Lgp9Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"First dates are best done over drinks or coffee: &#34;Getting to know you&#34; chit chat and accidental arm touches. Second dates should be more active and unique. Sacco&#39;s is the best second date in Boston.<br><br>The bar menu is extensive, the bowling (Candlepin!) is incredibly fun, and the pizza is out of this f@&amp;%#$g world. Consume all three in large, irresponsible quantities.<br><br>If you want to get a lane, even on a weeknight, you&#39;ll have to show up early. The wait time is very variable (I&#39;ve waited 30 minutes to 3 hours for the same 8PM weeknight lane), so be sure to check in as soon as you can. The host will typically take your phone number so you can roam Davis Square if (for some reason) you don&#39;t like pizza and beer.<br><br>There is a full bar in the back that is worth a trip on its own. Often full of young professionals, the bar has a rotating menu of craft beers and a great bourbon selection. If you are looking for a good happy hour spot, look no further.<br><br>The pizzas are large - be warned - and addictive. You get to choose your cheese, topping, sauce, and dough. Naturally, this yields many combinations, and the menu highlights some of the best. Always go for the house sauce - it is a little more expensive but worth it.<br><br>Prices are fair. People are great. Atmosphere is the best in Somerville. Easier to get a lane weeknights than weekends, but this place is worth a trip any day of the week.",
