"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Bcf-FwHH_URhZq70IEl40Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Just had my second take out experience from Wang&#39;s and the food is great.<br><br>Background on me:  Experienced Chinese takeout eater.  Always try things twice before passing judgement.  If the vegetables are nothing but onion and celery with the lone broccoli for colour, the odds of a third visit from me are nil.<br><br>Decor and ambiance - Just about none.  This place will accommodate the eat-in eater, but seems like more of a take-out place.  Very fast for takeout - from order to pick up was 20 min and I have to ay I think it may have been waiting a few minutes.<br><br>Taste:  Delicious.  None of the flavours is too overpowering and the items listed as spicy were - without burning my mouth off.  Also, not too greasy.  Having tried it twice and found consistency in deliciousity (not a real word...I know), this is my new go to Chinese takeout place.  Do not like the spring rolls though, not flavourful enough, but stuffed with veg and super crispy.<br><br>Freshness and quality :  All of the food tastes very fresh, the Broccoli was crisp and green and lovely.  I wonder if the baby corn in the veggie delight came from a can, but I can hardly fault them for that...I have never seen it in the supermarket fresh.  The chicken was a mix of white and dark meat in the stir fried dishes which is nice.  Noodles were tender.  Tofu was firm.  YUM.<br><br>Portion size:  Perfect for sharing.  Each entrée could comfortably be shared by 4 and at between $6-9 that is impressive.   I am writing having finished dinner and I am stuffed, my wife is stuffed, my kid is running around and not answering questions, but there are enough leftovers to last at least another full meal.<br><br>Dishes ordered (over two visits):  Vegetable delight (8/10), springroll (4/10), Kong Pao Chicken (its they spell it - I am used to Kung Pao - 10/10), General Gao Chicken (10/10 - I liked that they served it with red pepper), Veggie fried rice (7.5/10), Chicken lo mein (9/10), Sesame Tofu (10/10 - kid loved it), beef with broccoli (8.5/10)<br><br>Summary:  Great food, great price, great portions.  My new go to Chinese takeout place.",
