"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/r5wu6QnrqYA6JJzHTDqs6g/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"Alright, how do I say this, I&#39;m a diehard Yankee fan and everytime I&#39;m in Boston, I get shit for being a Yankee fan, which is to be expected. Anyways, McGreevey&#39;s is a must stop for me everytime I&#39;m in Boston as its becoming my favorite bar in Boston. So a diehard Yankee fan who always comes to a bar that was named after Nuff Ced McGreevy, a passionate Red Sox fan and a bar that has Red Sox memorabilia all over the place and a sign saying &#39;1200 steps to Fenway&#39;. Does that sound messed up to you cause it sure as hell sounds messed up to me, even as I write this review.<br><br>Drinks are reasonably priced I think, even though I just stick with the cheap and lousy beers but like other reviewers said, bartenders are cool, they&#39;re always nice to talk to, in fact last time I was there some guy was yelling at a bartender to get me another beer and the bartender responded by saying &#34;finish the three drinks in front of you!&#34; and I&#39;ve been here a few times and the bartenders have always given me flack for my team allegiances but its all in good fun. The food is alright, I&#39;ve eaten meals here before and it&#39;s pretty darn good for bar food.<br><br>I can&#39;t say this enough, whenever I&#39;m in Boston, I&#39;ll probably be here sitting at the bar and talking with the bartenders. This place is like that place for me, you like it so much and you always go there and while I&#39;m not completely sure why I always go there, I can pretty much list the following as the main reasons-<br><br>1) Good crowd<br>2) Decently priced beer<br>3) Awesome bartenders<br>4) Oh yeah, owned by the Dropkick Murphys, one of my favorite bands. You just can&#39;t beat that<br><br>Yeah, so if anyone wants to visit Boston with me, know ahead of time that we&#39;re gonna end up here at some point drinking beers.",
