"reviewcomment":"Brought my mother here for Sunday brunch - our meals were delicious and the service was first rate. <br><br>My mother ordered the scrambled eggs with fried oysters and it came with a nice green salad on the side and was delightful. I&#39;m not big into eggs, so I decided to take a little gamble and get the fish cakes. I was not disappointed - they were crispy, flavorful, and filled with fish and spices laid on a bed of greens and homemade baked beans. Yum! My boyfriend joined as well and had to scoot early - they were really accommodating in getting his breakfast sandwich prepared really quickly and apparently it was &#34;best breakfast sandwich&#34; he&#39;s ever had. <br><br>I believe it was the owner who was so pleasant and made us feel right at home. Also, the plants and floral arrangements in the restaurant were out of control. There is a huge wall installation brimming with plants and a beautifully arranged epic vase of cherry blossom branches in full bloom. <br><br>We really enjoyed our morning there. This was my first visit and I plan to go for dinner soon.  If the dinner is as wonderful as this brunch I&#39;ll update my review to five stars for sure!",
