"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Please note: My last visit was in 2012 so things may have changed. Please read other more recent reviews to get a feel for what this place is like now.<br><br>- - -<br><br>This is an authentic (the staff are actually Thai which is rare), casual, hole-in-the-wall gem of a Thai restaurant. Their portions may be annoyingly small, their prices may continue to increase, and the restaurant may not be much of a looker, but just thinking about their food will make you salivate uncontrollably! This is another Boston restaurant I&#39;d trek through hail and snow for, when I was living in Boston. One way to get the most out of their portion sizing for noodle dishes, is to order the noodle dish with thin rice noodles. The cost is the same but they will give you more for some reason. I used to order Pad See Ew with thin rice noodles all the time and I&#39;d get almost 1/3 more than the usual portions when I did. The Pad Thai, Rad Nah, and Pad Kee Mao are fantastic too. So are the rice dishes. In fact, I can&#39;t remember having been disappointed by any of their dishes so why not try them all! :)<br><br>Food: 5/5 -- superb and authentic!<br>Service: 5/5 -- attentive and efficient, though don&#39;t expect any frills<br>Atmosphere: 3/5 -- decent, casual, nothing remarkable<br><br>Overall: 5/5 -- exceptional!",
