"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Teriyaki House is solid!  Unassuming Chinese/Japanese take out place (there are seats, but I wouldn&#39;t eat there) with a lot of food options, great prices, and good quality.  That&#39;s what I expect when I go there, and that&#39;s what I get.  We always order what we think is a reasonable amount, but always have leftovers.  My favorite kind of place.<br><br>The only reason Teriyaki House isn&#39;t 5-stars, is because the cashiers taking the order don&#39;t typically speak English very well, and I have had my order wrong once or twice.  But I have learned my lesson, and really listen when they read the order back to me.<br><br>You see them making food, and I love that transparency.  The sushi, yes sushi, is good and reasonably priced (fortunately I&#39;m not a sushi snob, so TH is great for my sushi fix).  They even have a bowl of fortune cookies on the counter, so you can take as many as you need.<br><br>Set your expectations, go there, and enjoy!",
