"reviewcomment":"I tried this place out because I had some Foodler credits I wanted to use, and it had free delivery with an $8 minimum which is practically nothing. I ordered a large hamburger pizza and it got here within 30 minutes, so I can&#39;t complain about delivery time.<br><br>The pizza itself tastes like a better version of Papa John&#39;s pizza (take that however you want, I personally think it&#39;s the best national pizza chain). They LOAD it with toppings, so you probably want to think carefully when you add toppings. I think I may have actually preferred just cheese or pepperoni because the ground beef/hamburger they use is a little bland. The crusts are doughy, and that&#39;s just how I like it. It was also really cheesy, which is never a bad thing. I enjoyed the pizza overall, but I&#39;d probably make a different choice next time.<br><br>Overall, the pizza was good, it was cheap (about $15 total including tip), and it was delivered quickly. You could do a lot worse than here.",
