"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I have to level with you guys. I&#39;ve been to Teranga twice now and I&#39;m still not sure how to describe Senegalese food.  There doesn&#39;t seem to be one signature dish or ingredient that (to me) typifies the cuisine.  With that said, both meals I had here were delicious.  I guess a lot of the dishes are comprised of braised meats and vegetables, but that&#39;s not saying a whole lot.<br><br>The one signature item I had both times was this combination of two drinks -- one (or maybe both?) are made from the baobab fruit.  I was told by a friend who had spent some time in Senegal that I was supposed to mix the two, though mostly I ended up just drinking the one that tasted like creamsicles almost exclusively.  That&#39;s right: liquid creamsicles.  It&#39;s every bit as decadent as it sounds.<br><br>Even if you have no idea what Senegalese food is like, give Teranga a chance.  There aren&#39;t any bizarre spices or esoteric meat products that might scare away less adventurous diners.",
