"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Nice Texas-style BBQ in Brookline Village<br><br>Located in the heart of Brookline Village, the Village Smokehouse offers fairly authentic Texas-style BBQ.  The ambiance is simple but fun.  You can see the BBQ &#34;pit&#34; as you walk in and from your table.  The service is friendly and efficient.<br><br>The Smokehouse offers a variety of BBQ specialties.  For appetizers, stand-out offerings include the buffalo fried shrimp, the potato skins, and the the buffalo chicken.  However, these are pretty standard compared with what you might find in a good pub.  The Smokehouse shines through its BBQ.  The beef brisket is lean but juicy with subtle seasoning that is brought out by their tomato-based BBQ sauce.  Their BBQ sauce is tangy and smoky.  The pulled pork is tender moist and comes alive with the BBQ sauce.  I would have to say their pork ribs are probably the best they have to offer.  Some reviews on Yelp have mentioned that the ribs are a bit dry.  I would tend to agree but that is not that unusual for slow-cooked Texas-style BBQ.  The flavor of the ribs is excellent, and dry or not, the meat still loosens from the bone easily.  In my travels through the BBQ-Belt down South, many of the cooks at authentic highly-rated BBQ joints contend that if the meat just falls off the bone, it&#39;s overcooked.<br><br>The Smokehouse offers baked beans and cornbread complementary with your meal.    You also get a choice of sides.  The mash potatoes are quite good.<br><br>All-in-all, the Smokehouse is a great option for Texas-style BBQ in Brookline and one of the better places in the Boston area.  It&#39;s not going to beat true Texas-style BBQ that you might get down South, but it&#39;s not that far off either.",
