"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Diners = love.  And Kelly&#39;s is no exception.<br><br>After passing this on a million runs and weekend strolls, I finally went in for breakfast today.  I was looking for something more personal that Soundbites and Ball Square, with better hash browns (fried mashed potatoes are SO not the same thing).  <br><br>Kelly&#39;s definitely lived up to this vision.  The waitress acted like she knew us before we even sat down (&#34;you both like coffee, right?  you know where the menus are&#34; etc) even though we&#39;d never been here before - adorable.  The food options are not overly extensive but that just makes it easier to pick.<br><br>My sister and I both got the &#34;famous&#34; homemade corned beef hash and poached eggs.  Both were a lot less greasy/salty than usual diner grub - almost to a fault.  I would rather add a little of my own salt (and skip the fat altogether) but it was still a little strange to have my tastebuds turned in this direction.  Add a pinch of salt and pepper and you have me clearing my plate in record time.<br><br>I love the scene here - the other patrons with their huge hair, the friendly staff, the non-working jukebox.  I&#39;ll definitely be back - and by then, the waitress should definitely know my order. <br><br>Note: cash only, but there&#39;s an ATM in the entrance.",
