"reviewcomment":"Had dinner here tonight with a friend. I&#39;m a fan! Had reservations for two for 7:00 pm but when we informed the hostess that a last minute third party may show up we were immediately accommodated from a table for two to a table for four. The restaurant has two levels, both attractively accented with dark woods, brick walls and great views of the city streets. A very comfortable atmosphere. <br>       Our waiter (alas, I forget his name) was very efficient. Prompt with orders, informative about the menu, always about in the background eyeballing our table but never intrusive. There when we needed him and not when we didn&#39;t. <br>         We started out with the antipasto platter for two. A delicious mix of tangy marinated vegetables, meats and cheeses. A perfectly proportioned appetizer for two people to whet the appetite. The complimentary bread and olive oil/balsamic vinegar dipping sauce was a great go-with. For entrees, my friend ordered the scallops puttanesca, which she said was very good. I had the gnocchi Bolognese which was amazing. I had always been on the fence about gnocchi, having had mostly pastey globs of garbage. Bacco reminded me how fantastically great a correctly made gnocchi can taste and the Bolognese sauce was spot on delicious. Order it, you won&#39;t be sorry...........make sure to have your server add the grated parmesan cheese and pepper!<br>             No dessert, as we were both more than satisfied. Simply finished off the meal with a simple cup of coffee and left feeling we go our money&#39;s worth. Bacco&#39;s lost one star for it&#39;s singular unisex bathroom. Not the most attractive and promotes long waits. Recommended.",
