"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/pLC5hBb63KooGl2EIXkUDw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"You know, I&#39;m a little surprised by how negative a lot of these reviews are.  I&#39;ve been to Moksa twice, and each time I&#39;ve had a positive experience.<br><br>My bf and I went last night for the patio event, but it was kind of rainy and windy, so we chose to sit at the bar instead.<br><br>Did you know that from 5-7pm every weekday, they have ALL YOU CAN EAT SUSHI for $15?  Yeah.  They do.  The sushi menu for all-you-can eat is a bit smaller -- <br>Spicy Tuna Roll, Shrimp Tempura Roll, California Roll, Philly Roll, Seaweed Samba, Maimo Roll, Salmon &amp; Avocado Roll, and Cucumber &amp; Avocado Roll.<br><br>My boyfriend and I ate the spicy tuna, philly roll, maimo, roll, and salmon &amp; avocado roll (don&#39;t worry we ate several servings of each...definitely got our money&#39;s worth!).<br>The maimo roll is sweet potato tempura, and it was the surprise winner of the night.  The sweet potato was still warm and a little crunch from the tempura -- really delightful.  I always love a good spicy tuna and philly roll, too.  We also got a couple of the $1 menu apps -- dumpling, chicken skewer, and gyoza.  All delicious little bites.  There was a special $2 paneer tikka from the patio event that was also nice (although a little small and should probably have just been $1).<br><br>Did you know that they have wine ON TAP?  Yes.  I&#39;d never heard of it either.  It was a Cote de Rhone and I would have had more than one glass, but the bartender was light with her hand and I didn&#39;t think it was worth another $8 for a short glass.<br><br>All in all, the food was really great and I&#39;m only giving it 4 stars because service was a little slow.  Otherwise, everyone there was very friendly!",
