"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/7GBPiAZQBRqbbtxM-j8QjQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Ran out of space, so on to the next page!<br><br>*** 12/2013 visit ***<br><br>Wild Mushroom Burger* whipped blue cheese, caramelized onions 11 <br>seasoned waffle fries 3 <br><br>I wasn&#39;t crazy about the burger though the waffle fries were fine.<br><br>*** 1/2014 visit ***<br><br>I&#39;ve been wanting to try Blue&#39;s Pumpkin Bisque, pumpkin seeds, poached apples $7, but they were out the day I tried to order it.  But today, I wanted something a bit more filling.  Maybe it is all for the best, since I actually prefer butternut squash to pumpkin, and am oft dissatisfied.  Yet, I will still try another day...<br><br>For this visit, I ordered a repeat of two menu items I&#39;ve enjoyed in the past - the Crispy Shrimp Tacos, mango cucumber, spicy aioli, shredded cabbage $14 and the side of arugula $2 with some grilled pineapple tossed on.<br><br>When I got back with my take-out tote in hand, I realized I had somehow scored an upgrade, as there was some strips of meat product scattered on top of the arugula along with the 4 pineapple pieces.  Turns out the kitchen had erred and made a full Arugula Salad (balsamic vinaigrette, fresh mozzarella, marinated tomatoes, crispy pepperoni $10) topped with my requested pineapple.  So, no, they weren&#39;t looking for a missing arugula salad that had wandered off when they were unawares.<br><br>The portion of arugula in the salad was about the same as what I had received when they made me the $2 arugula side on a previous visit.  On that was a healthy (ha!) scattering of the crispy strips of pepperoni, and a few of the wrinkled tomatoes.  The two fat slices of mozz, each halved, were hidden beneath the field of green.  I&#39;m not sure that this salad would fill my luncheon appetite, but I am the one who can&#39;t figure out how folks can be satisfied with just salad (unless the greens are topped with loads of a variety of vibrant veggies and crunch factors!), but I think I prefer this salad with the touch of sweetness lent by the addition of the grilled pineapple.<br><br>The shrimp tacos (numbering 3) were once again filled with two large meaty crustaceans apiece fried in a light foamy style batter, but this time the spice shined through a bit more clearly.  No milk, so I made do with water and a mouthful of arugula.<br><br>Oh no!  My Yelp identity has been compromised!  Yes, I am the one who posts loads of photos on Yelp.  Hopefully they&#39;ll still be nice to me anyways.<br><br>*** 3/2014 visit ***<br><br>I guess the Pumpkin Bisque pumpkin seeds, poached apples 7 is not to be.<br><br>Today they had the same but in Butternut Squash, for the same price.<br><br>I ordered it as take out.  The portion size was okay in the plastic tub, but the container was not nearly filled to the brim.<br><br>The soup is creamy thick, but savory.  I figured out why most soups don&#39;t float my boat - I&#39;m trying to relive an old butternut squash soup experience of yesteryear that had made such an impact on my tastebuds...  Oh well.  But this one was okay.  The pumpkin seeds and sweet poached apple balls (5) added texture and contrasting flavors.",
