"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve been going to Bistro 5 every year for the past three years for birthdays and other special events. When I had my wedding dinner here last summer with family, they put together an amazing, cohesive, and elegant menu that really emphasized the ingredients (panko-crusted green tomatoes &amp; duck confit stood out). It was one of the best meals of my life and I&#39;m so thankful to the restaurant for making such a beautiful day even more memorable!<br><br>I always have their tastings because it is honestly one of the best tasting menu deals in Boston. The food is consistently delicious - I still think about a parpadelle I had once (with boar I think). Their wine pairings are always top notch (with their wine guy going to wine conventions to test out and stock up on good bottles) and they give very generous pours. <br><br>Above all else, Bistro 5 provides exemplary service - always professional and without any pretentiousness or elitism. The servers are knowledgeable about the dishes and wines, quick to replace silverware and fill up your water, and attentive.",
