"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/5jJAc8uYP4d-ppi-QRcCuw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Crossroads is the type of Irish pub you know you will like as soon as you walk in. This is NOT the old Crossroads, as the new owners have put a lot of sweat and love into the place. Both upstairs and the first floor have been completely renovated, you might not recognize it as Crossroads. Overall, the atmosphere is comfortable and after spending last Saturday night in the upstairs bar, we know we will be back. Plenty of sports on the TVs and the background music is great; they definitely know their music and what to spin.<br><br>It seems everything has been expanded: the menu, the beer list, the Irish whiskey selection and the drink list. A few familiar faces still work at Crossroads, but the new bartender - Steve - impressed us. He knew his drinks, and he knew how to make them well. He is a &#34;professional bartender&#34; - friendly, knowledgeable and dedicated to making you enjoy a great night. The manager - Kristen - introduced herself and was very kind and helpful. This is what I call an &#34;all hands&#34; pub, as everyone we met was busy; trying to make sure everyone around us had a great time.<br><br>The menu reflected the environment: Truly, a real Irish menu at a true Irish pub. The old Crossroads relied heavily on burgers; this menu is much more than beef. And the prices are definitely competitive. The two waitresses - Jesse and Kayla - are easy on the eyes, and professional in every way. They took the time to explain the new items on the menu, and made suggestions for my wary friend. I&#39;m going to try a few more items before making my own suggestions to you. <br><br>My suggestion: Come to the new Crossroads, give it a try. It&#39;s definitively NOT the old Crossroads - it is better!<br><br>OPEN - new website: <a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.crossroads-irishpub.com&amp;s=3742545c4aed99a9a61b5a7519b7c08aaca74d327efc0edc9e2a4d72dd3a132c' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>crossroads-irishpub.com</a>",
