"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Worth every dime!... In planning my trip to Boston many yelp reviews insisted that I must try Pauli&#39;s  for the experience of a great lobster roll. <br><br>As soon as I landed I had the cab driver take me straight to Little Italy where Pauli&#39;s is located. We entered Pauli&#39;s around 1pm on Thursday and to my surprise the joint didn&#39;t have many customers considering it was lunch time but the workers behind the counter worked as if they were swamped with orders. <br><br>As soon as we entered I walked to the counter and ordered with out looking at the menu but my friend however took her precious time reviewing and inquiring about the different selections of lobster creations that they had. We sat down and not even 10 minutes later our orders came out. To my surprise my lobster roll came loaded with lumps and lumps of lobster meat. Once my friend opened her container I became super jealous... she ordered a lobster grilled cheese sandwich. .. whaaaat???? Where they do that? I had to taste and I was even more jealous because it was sooooo delicious. <br><br>Overall,  both selections were to die for. I spent $17 for my lobster roll which came with bag of chips and she spent $18 on her grilled cheese lobster sandwich that came with fries.<br><br>If you visit Boston anytime soon you need to stop by Pauli&#39;s",
