"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Coffee on a good, bad, or ugly day with music that&#39;ll keep you talking or writing or drinking more coffee. I&#39;ve spent a fair amount of my afternoons sitting around the cafe. Sometimes it gets a bit too crowded here and no seats can be found. I&#39;ll excuse it as a sign that their business is doing their job: bringing in repeat customers and good conversation. Wait around for ten or fifteen minutes and a seat will turn up (on a cold day you&#39;ll have a nice warm seat!). <br><br>As for the food, I really enjoy their bagels and (especially) their cream cheese. I believe they make it themselves? Definitely go for the veggie or jalapeno, as those are the bold flavors that&#39;ll make your bagel experience that much more bagel-y. My roommates are fans of the Allston Sunrise and haven&#39;t really ventured beyond that because it&#39;s their favorite. What I think Refuge does is it hooks the customer on one item, making it hard to resist the feeling when those taste buds are yearning for familiar deliciousness.<br><br>Give it a go, be adventurous. The menu has a bunch of options and no matter what it won&#39;t be too harsh on your wallet.",
