"reviewcomment":"Abby Lane is a great spot to hit up before a show at the Wilbur. The food and atmosphere was great and it&#39;s right across the street, so it&#39;s super convenient. <br><br>We popped in a little after 6PM on a weekday before a show at the Wilbur. The place was busy, but not jam packed. Since we didn&#39;t have a reservation, we sat at the bar on the main level. (Apparently there is also a lounge and bar on the second level, but we didn&#39;t get a chance to check it out.)<br><br>The cocktail and beer options were good and plentiful. The food options looked pretty excellent. We both opted for burgers - mine with bacon and provolone, his was just a regular cheeseburger. Both were perfectly cooked - cooked evenly medium rare throughout, which made me very happy. The fries were crisp on the outside and fluffy potato-heaven on the inside. Yum. <br><br>Oh! Pre-meal, we were served complimentary house made blue potato chips with house made french onion dip. It was addictive. <br><br>The service was prompt and friendly. Our server knew we were on a schedule and even though she was busy, she was on top of things. <br><br>If I had more time, I would have loved to have tried more drinks off their menu. Good to know there&#39;s a reliable spot for eats!",
