"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/s-XUfOer37iwI8BxiCEU5A/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Enjoyed an absolutely amazing night as a guest of a private tasting event at Troquet. A small gang of us, and a bundle of French wine took up at the bar and knocked down a fabulous evening.  <br><br>Chef Hebert chose a pair of Suckling Pigs to roast for us while we drank our way through a few killer bottles of wine.  The wine list here is absolutely top notch by the way, offering vintage selections from the 1970&#39;s and beyond.  A 1996 Volnay Coche Dury 1er Cru, pulled right from the list, had a soft floral character that challenges description. Great bottle of wine. <br><br>GM/Owner Chris Campbell was a fine and gracious host, the bar staff extraordinary and exemplary.  And the food, from my Chilled Maine Lobster Crêpe, dressed with vibrantly bright tomatoes; to the roasted pig, served a la Cassoulet over white beans and Boudin blanc, did not disappoint.<br><br>As if we needed further indulgence, we finished with a share of roasted Pig Cheeks and a sauce from the drippings of the roasted pork. A crispy, near candy, finish to a great night of dining.<br><br>A+",
