"categorystrlist":"American (New),         American (Traditional)",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Tod_uy9isoIuf6aUSgE2RQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I had dinner here on a Friday night and was happy with just about everything.   I think we had a 7pm reservation and were seated immediately in the back room which was cozy but not cramped.   From our table we could see a cute dining area in the backyard.  If it&#39;s Kitchen&#39;s, I&#39;d love to come back to eat out there. <br>The house bread was pretty fantastic - pillowy rolls with a sprinkle of salt on top.  I chose the &#34;Sallet&#34; to start - a colorful and delicious mix of greens, eggs, sweet and tart fruit, loved it.  He got clams casino which isn&#39;t really my thing, but the clams were  served on plate of salt and spilling over with crispy bacon stuffing and I couldn&#39;t resist 1 or 2.  <br>Several appetizers looked appealing to me and I considered forgoing the entree for a few small plates (I really wanted a full plate of duck fat brussels sprouts!) but I ended up ordering the crispy half duck since it came with a side of brussels and a big endorsement from our server.   I took the chef&#39;s recommendation for medium rare, and the meat was beautifully tender, but I really would have preferred a crispier skin and a bit more salt.  So the duck was a bit lackluster on its own, but the smoky bed of lentils and baby brussels saved it..  <br>He got the pork and beans.  Of the 3 or 4 different styles of pork, I liked the offal meatball the most.  He must have liked the rib because I didn&#39;t get to taste any.  We both agreed that the sausage and pulled pork were a little bland. <br>The doughnuts for dessert were a big winner, with tangy dollops of jam and vanilla.  <br>Overall, a very good experience.  Some things better than others, but great service and lots on the menu left to try.",
