"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"A hidden gem in a dumpy alley. The front door was barely visible, even while standing in front of it, because there&#39;s literal dump trucks in the alley. Good thing it is in the heart of downtown. Hubs and I were wandering around looking for something to cure our hangover...Barracuda Tavern picked us right up. The place was generally empty, but it didn&#39;t feel like a huge cave or anything because the place is small and divey, like an upstairs beach bar in Key West. Speaking of Key West, they had conch fritters...they were delicious, but I&#39;m glad I wasn&#39;t expecting to share these. The order only came with three, but they are dang good. Then I got some disco fries...basically fries covered with a ridiculous amount of melted cheese, gravy, and bacon (I was hungover, don&#39;t judge me). I could have eaten these all day. To be honest, I don&#39;t remember what my husband ordered, because I was in cheese fry heaven. <br><br>This place is definitely a far cry from some of the touristy or hip places in downtown Boston. I think if I lived in Boston, I&#39;d frequent this place for the dope food and summertime vibe.",
