"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OzCBFDUvvb4mSUfG9W6D3w/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Crazy, crazy good.  Redd&#39;s is a foodie&#39;s dream in a laid-back, casual, Sunday morning, sleep-in-the-eye kind of way.  <br><br>On this rainy, dreary Sunday everyone apparently woke up with the same idea of coming here - it was packed.  The host did all he could to collect names, and reassure people the wait wouldn&#39;t be too long, even with large parties.  I believe when you go to brunch on a Sunday, it can only mean good things if there is a wait!<br><br>After being seated, our server quickly brought us coffee and went over the amazing specials (as if deciding what to order wasn&#39;t difficult enough based on the menu).  I was told the fried avocado was a must, and far be it from me to argue.  Amazing, creamy, delicious and wicked.  Between my friend and I we had omelets, eggs, grits, bacon, biscuits and home-made donuts on the table.  Everything was well cooked and absolutely scrumptious.  My &#34;tapas&#34; omelet (one of the specials that day) had scallops, shrimp and other deliciousness.  (I cannot recall the manner that the fillings were prepared, I&#39;d only had one cup of coffee at this point..)  The biscuits... omg - I would eat a van full of those.  Even the grits were creamy and yummy.  The service was a bit slow and hectic, but it was a rainy Sunday, I had delicious food on the table, a never empty cup of coffee and great company.  Why would I want to rush that?<br><br>I would not only come back again, but am actively seeking to book a date with friends in the near future.",
