"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Yummy and affordable shawarma!<br>The perfect end to an afternoon at the MFA, Boston Shawarma is a quick walk from the museum. There were about six tables and a seating counter next to the window. It&#39;s a low key place, and it&#39;s about the food, not the atmosphere. On top of the desserts case they had free samples of some kind of sweet. I don&#39;t remember the name of it, but it was really good, and you could take as many pieces as you wanted. <br><br>The lamb shawarma wrap me and my boyfriend each had was big - one would have been enough to feed two - but I ate all of mine because it was so good. It is spicy; so be forewarned - and they didn&#39;t have any free water that I could see (although they did sell bottled water). It also gets messy, since the sauce and some of the fillings tend to fall out as you are eating. Just get some extra napkins and you&#39;ll be fine.<br><br>For dessert, we had the basbousa and the baklava. Very very sweet, as Middle Eastern desserts tend to be, but it was a great end to the spicy meal. The rice pudding looked really good too, but I didn&#39;t get a chance to try it. <br><br>I&#39;d definitely go back! Shawarma was absolutely worth it.",
