"categorystrlist":"Mediterranean",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/xvyTR-oxO8nx-9DeVrtAww/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"4 stars for food, 5 for ambiance and service. Scutra looks like not-much from the outside -- almost a strip-mall-type location, but inside the place is well-decorated, not overly lighted, and quiet. That&#39;s the physical ambiance. In terms of a warm welcome and attentive service, it was a standout. Dinner began with crusty bread and a herbed good-quality olive oil. Cocktails($10 range) were imaginative and not fruit-punchy -- mine simply had vodka, gin, and lillet with a twist of orange; and the wine list was short but nice, with enough choices by the glass ($7-9 range). The food was imaginative, too, including a duck and sundried fruit strudel, a not-rice-heavy paella, a lamb scallopin, plus nice desserts. A one-page, thoughtully constructed, and correctly spelled menu (for once!). I&#39;ve had tastes that stood out more than these -- though they were certainly very good indeed -- and the overall experience is definitely one I&#39;ll repeat. I don&#39;t know whether it&#39;s a family- or chef-owned place, but it felt like it, with all the care and pride that such a designation implies.",
