"reviewcomment":"If you were born in the Boston-area, you&#39;ve probably spent many a family parties here . Did someone get confirmed? Go to the North End. Did your boyfriend dump you and your slightly awkward Dad want to do something nice for you? Your probably split a pie at the Medford location. <br><br>Bostonians love talking about the good ol&#39; days when Regina&#39;s meant going to the North End, not to a stop in the &#39;burbs. My brother enjoys devouring the pasta at the Medford location whilst simultaneously complaining that the &#34;real&#34; Regina&#39;s doesn&#39;t offer anything except pizza. These points are valid, there is something magical about going to the North End- filled with men sucking on cigars and the smell of fresh pizza in the air - but the Medford location has its own charm. If you are a Medford-onian, you will ALWAYS bump into someone you know - the bartender probably was in your homeroom, and the man screaming furiously at the TV, was your CCD teacher. <br><br>The pizza is solid. I always just get the cheese, but my parents enjoy going on date night here and spilting the shrimp and spinach. The bar is also a great way to watch the &#34;game.&#34;",
